43   @sharable private[this] var nextId = 0
44 
45   implicit def eqType: Eq[Type, Type] = Eq
46 
47   /** Main class representing types.
48    *
49    *  The principal subclasses and sub-objects are as follows:
50    *
51    *  ```none
52    *  Type -+- ProxyType --+- NamedType ----+--- TypeRef
53    *        |              |                 \
54    *        |              +- SingletonType-+-+- TermRef
55    *        |              |                |
56    *        |              |                +--- ThisType
57    *        |              |                +--- SuperType
58    *        |              |                +--- ConstantType
59    *        |              |                +--- TermParamRef
60    *        |              |                +----RecThis
61    *        |              |                +--- SkolemType
62    *        |              +- TypeParamRef
63    *        |              +- RefinedOrRecType -+-- RefinedType
64    *        |              |                   -+-- RecType
65    *        |              +- AppliedType
66    *        |              +- TypeBounds
67    *        |              +- ExprType
68    *        |              +- AnnotatedType
69    *        |              +- TypeVar
70    *        |              +- HKTypeLambda
71    *        |
72    *        +- GroundType -+- AndType
73    *                       +- OrType
74    *                       +- MethodOrPoly ---+-- PolyType
75    *                                          +-- MethodType ---+- ImplicitMethodType
76    *                       |                                    +- JavaMethodType
77    *                       +- ClassInfo
78    *                       |
79    *                       +- NoType
80    *                       +- NoPrefix
81    *                       +- ErrorType
82    *                       +- WildcardType
83    *  ```
84    *
85    *  Note: please keep in sync with copy in `docs/docs/internals/type-system.md`.
86    */
87   abstract class Type extends DotClass with Hashable with printing.Showable {
88

91     // debug only: a unique identifier for a type
92     val uniqId = {
93       nextId = nextId + 1
94 //      if (nextId == 19555)

96       nextId
97     }

99     /** Is this type different from NoType? */
100     def exists: Boolean = true
101 
102     /** This type, if it exists, otherwise `that` type */
103     def orElse(that: => Type) = if (exists) this else that
104 
105     /** Is this type a value type? */
106     final def isValueType: Boolean = this.isInstanceOf[ValueType]
107 
108     /** Is the is value type or type lambda? */
109     final def isValueTypeOrLambda: Boolean = isValueType || this.isInstanceOf[TypeLambda]
110 
111     /** Does this type denote a stable reference (i.e. singleton type)? */
112     final def isStable(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = stripTypeVar match {
113       case tp: TermRef => tp.termSymbol.isStable && tp.prefix.isStable || tp.info.isStable
114       case _: SingletonType | NoPrefix => true
115       case tp: RefinedOrRecType => tp.parent.isStable
116       case tp: ExprType => tp.resultType.isStable
117       case tp: AnnotatedType => tp.tpe.isStable
118       case _ => false
119     }
120 
121     /** Is this type a (possibly refined or applied or aliased) type reference
122      *  to the given type symbol?
123      *  @sym  The symbol to compare to. It must be a class symbol or abstract type.
124      *        It makes no sense for it to be an alias type because isRef would always
125      *        return false in that case.
126      */
127     def isRef(sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = stripAnnots.stripTypeVar match {
128       case this1: TypeRef =>
129         this1.info match { // see comment in Namer#typeDefSig
130           case TypeAlias(tp) => tp.isRef(sym)
131           case _ => this1.symbol eq sym
132         }
133       case this1: RefinedOrRecType =>
134         this1.parent.isRef(sym)
135       case this1: AppliedType =>
136         val this2 = this1.dealias
137         if (this2 ne this1) this2.isRef(sym)
138         else this1.underlying.isRef(sym)
139       case _ => false
140     }
141 
142     /** Is this type a (neither aliased nor applied) reference to class `sym`? */
143     def isDirectRef(sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = stripTypeVar match {
144       case this1: TypeRef =>
145         this1.name == sym.name && // avoid forcing info if names differ
146         (this1.symbol eq sym)
147       case _ =>
148         false
149     }
150 
151     /** Does this type refer exactly to class symbol `sym`, instead of to a subclass of `sym`?
152      *  Implemented like `isRef`, but follows more types: all type proxies as well as and- and or-types
153      */
154     private[Types] def isTightPrefix(sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = stripTypeVar match {
155       case tp: NamedType => tp.info.isTightPrefix(sym)
156       case tp: ClassInfo => tp.cls eq sym
157       case tp: Types.ThisType => tp.cls eq sym
158       case tp: TypeProxy => tp.underlying.isTightPrefix(sym)
159       case tp: AndType => tp.tp1.isTightPrefix(sym) && tp.tp2.isTightPrefix(sym)
160       case tp: OrType => tp.tp1.isTightPrefix(sym) || tp.tp2.isTightPrefix(sym)
161       case _ => false
162     }
163 
164     /** Is this type an instance of a non-bottom subclass of the given class `cls`? */
165     final def derivesFrom(cls: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = {
166       def loop(tp: Type): Boolean = tp match {
167         case tp: TypeRef =>
168           val sym = tp.symbol
169           if (sym.isClass) sym.derivesFrom(cls) else loop(tp.superType): @tailrec
170         case tp: TypeProxy =>
171           loop(tp.underlying): @tailrec
172         case tp: AndType =>
173           loop(tp.tp1) || loop(tp.tp2): @tailrec
174         case tp: OrType =>
175           loop(tp.tp1) && loop(tp.tp2): @tailrec
176         case tp: JavaArrayType =>
177           cls == defn.ObjectClass
178         case _ =>
179           false
180       }
181       loop(this)
182     }
183 
184     /** True iff `symd` is a denotation of a class type parameter and the reference
185      *  `<this> . <symd>` is an actual argument reference, i.e. `this` is different
186      *  from the ThisType of `symd`'s owner.
187      */
188     def isArgPrefixOf(symd: SymDenotation)(implicit ctx: Context) =
189       symd.is(ClassTypeParam) && {
190         this match {
191           case tp: ThisType => tp.cls ne symd.owner
192           case _ => true
193         }
194       }
195 
196     /** Returns true if the type is a phantom type
197      *   - true if XYZ extends scala.Phantom and this type is upper bounded XYZ.Any
198      *   - false otherwise
199      */
200     final def isPhantom(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = phantomLatticeType.exists
201 
202     /** Returns the top type of the lattice
203      *   - XYX.Any if XYZ extends scala.Phantom and this type is upper bounded XYZ.Any
204      *   - scala.Any otherwise
205      */
206     final def topType(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
207       val lattice = phantomLatticeType
208       if (lattice.exists) lattice.select(tpnme.Any)
209       else defn.AnyType
210     }
211 
212     /** Returns the bottom type of the lattice
213      *   - XYZ.Nothing if XYZ extends scala.Phantom and this type is upper bounded XYZ.Any
214      *   - scala.Nothing otherwise
215      */
216     final def bottomType(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
217       val lattice = phantomLatticeType
218       if (lattice.exists) lattice.select(tpnme.Nothing)
219       else defn.NothingType
220     }
221 
222     /** Is this type exactly Nothing (no vars, aliases, refinements etc allowed)? */
223     def isBottomType(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = this match {
224       case tp: TypeRef =>
225         val sym = tp.symbol
226         (sym eq defn.NothingClass) || (sym eq defn.Phantom_NothingClass)
227       case _ => false
228     }
229 
230       /** Is this type exactly Any (no vars, aliases, refinements etc allowed)? */
231     def isTopType(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = this match {
232       case tp: TypeRef =>
233         val sym = tp.symbol
234         (sym eq defn.AnyClass) || (sym eq defn.Phantom_AnyClass)
235       case _ => false
236     }
237 
238     /** Returns the type of the phantom lattice (i.e. the prefix of the phantom type)
239       *   - XYZ if XYZ extends scala.Phantom and this type is upper bounded XYZ.Any
240       *   - NoType otherwise
241       */
242     private final def phantomLatticeType(implicit ctx: Context): Type = widen match {
243       case tp: ClassInfo if defn.isPhantomTerminalClass(tp.classSymbol) => tp.prefix
244       case tp: TypeProxy => tp.underlying.phantomLatticeType
245       case tp: AndOrType => tp.tp1.phantomLatticeType
246       case _ => NoType
247     }
248 
249     /** Is this type a (possibly aliased) singleton type? */
250     def isSingleton(implicit ctx: Context) = dealias.isInstanceOf[SingletonType]
251 
252     /** Is this type guaranteed not to have `null` as a value? */
253     final def isNotNull(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = this match {
254       case tp: ConstantType => tp.value.value != null
255       case tp: ClassInfo => !tp.cls.isNullableClass && tp.cls != defn.NothingClass
256       case tp: TypeBounds => tp.lo.isNotNull
257       case tp: TypeProxy => tp.underlying.isNotNull
258       case AndType(tp1, tp2) => tp1.isNotNull || tp2.isNotNull
259       case OrType(tp1, tp2) => tp1.isNotNull && tp2.isNotNull
260       case _ => false
261     }
262 
263     /** Is this type produced as a repair for an error? */
264     final def isError(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = stripTypeVar match {
265       case _: ErrorType => true
266       case tp => (tp.typeSymbol is Erroneous) || (tp.termSymbol is Erroneous)
267     }
268 
269     /** Is some part of this type produced as a repair for an error? */
270     final def isErroneous(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = existsPart(_.isError, forceLazy = false)
271 
272     /** Does the type carry an annotation that is an instance of `cls`? */
273     @tailrec final def hasAnnotation(cls: ClassSymbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = stripTypeVar match {
274       case AnnotatedType(tp, annot) => (annot matches cls) || (tp hasAnnotation cls)
275       case _ => false
276     }
277 
278     /** Does this type occur as a part of type `that`? */
279     final def occursIn(that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
280       that existsPart (this == _)
281 
282     /** Is this a type of a repeated parameter? */
283     def isRepeatedParam(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
284       typeSymbol eq defn.RepeatedParamClass
285 
286     /** Is this the type of a method that has a repeated parameter type as
287      *  last parameter type?
288      */
289     def isVarArgsMethod(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = stripPoly match {
290       case mt: MethodType => mt.paramInfos.nonEmpty && mt.paramInfos.last.isRepeatedParam
291       case _ => false
292     }
293 
294     /** Is this the type of a method with a leading empty parameter list?
295      */
296     def isNullaryMethod(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = stripPoly match {
297       case MethodType(Nil) => true
298       case _ => false
299     }
300 
301     /** Is this an alias TypeBounds? */
302     final def isAlias: Boolean = this.isInstanceOf[TypeAlias]
303 
304     /** Is this a MethodType which is from Java */
305     def isJavaMethod: Boolean = false
306 
307     /** Is this a MethodType which has implicit parameters */
308     def isImplicitMethod: Boolean = false

312     /** Returns true if there is a part of this type that satisfies predicate `p`.
313      */
314     final def existsPart(p: Type => Boolean, forceLazy: Boolean = true)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
315       new ExistsAccumulator(p, forceLazy).apply(false, this)
316 
317     /** Returns true if all parts of this type satisfy predicate `p`.
318      */
319     final def forallParts(p: Type => Boolean)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
320       !existsPart(!p(_))
321 
322     /** Performs operation on all parts of this type */
323     final def foreachPart(p: Type => Unit, stopAtStatic: Boolean = false)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit =
324       new ForeachAccumulator(p, stopAtStatic).apply((), this)
325 
326     /** The parts of this type which are type or term refs */
327     final def namedParts(implicit ctx: Context): collection.Set[NamedType] =
328       namedPartsWith(alwaysTrue)
329 
330     /** The parts of this type which are type or term refs and which
331      *  satisfy predicate `p`.
332      *
333      *  @param p                   The predicate to satisfy
334      *  @param excludeLowerBounds  If set to true, the lower bounds of abstract
335      *                             types will be ignored.
336      */
337     def namedPartsWith(p: NamedType => Boolean, excludeLowerBounds: Boolean = false)
338       (implicit ctx: Context): collection.Set[NamedType] =
339       new NamedPartsAccumulator(p, excludeLowerBounds).apply(mutable.LinkedHashSet(), this)
340 
341     /** Map function `f` over elements of an AndType, rebuilding with function `g` */
342     def mapReduceAnd[T](f: Type => T)(g: (T, T) => T)(implicit ctx: Context): T = stripTypeVar match {
343       case AndType(tp1, tp2) => g(tp1.mapReduceAnd(f)(g), tp2.mapReduceAnd(f)(g))
344       case _ => f(this)
345     }
346 
347     /** Map function `f` over elements of an OrType, rebuilding with function `g` */
348     final def mapReduceOr[T](f: Type => T)(g: (T, T) => T)(implicit ctx: Context): T = stripTypeVar match {
349       case OrType(tp1, tp2) => g(tp1.mapReduceOr(f)(g), tp2.mapReduceOr(f)(g))
350       case _ => f(this)
351     }

353 // ----- Associated symbols ----------------------------------------------
354 
355     /** The type symbol associated with the type */
356     @tailrec final def typeSymbol(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = this match {
357       case tp: TypeRef => tp.symbol
358       case tp: ClassInfo => tp.cls
359       case tp: SingletonType => NoSymbol
360       case tp: TypeProxy => tp.underlying.typeSymbol
361       case _ => NoSymbol
362     }
363 
364     /** The least class or trait of which this type is a subtype or parameterized
365      *  instance, or NoSymbol if none exists (either because this type is not a
366      *  value type, or because superclasses are ambiguous).
367      */
368     final def classSymbol(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = this match {
369       case ConstantType(constant) =>
370         constant.tpe.classSymbol: @tailrec
371       case tp: TypeRef =>
372         val sym = tp.symbol
373         if (sym.isClass) sym else tp.superType.classSymbol: @tailrec
374       case tp: ClassInfo =>
375         tp.cls
376       case tp: SingletonType =>
377         NoSymbol
378       case tp: TypeProxy =>
379         tp.underlying.classSymbol: @tailrec
380       case AndType(l, r) =>
381         val lsym = l.classSymbol
382         val rsym = r.classSymbol
383         if (lsym isSubClass rsym) lsym
384         else if (rsym isSubClass lsym) rsym
385         else NoSymbol
386       case OrType(l, r) => // TODO does not conform to spec
387         val lsym = l.classSymbol
388         val rsym = r.classSymbol
389         if (lsym isSubClass rsym) rsym
390         else if (rsym isSubClass lsym) lsym
391         else NoSymbol
392       case _ =>
393         NoSymbol
394     }
395 
396     /** The least (wrt <:<) set of class symbols of which this type is a subtype
397      */
398     final def classSymbols(implicit ctx: Context): List[ClassSymbol] = this match {
399       case tp: ClassInfo =>
400         tp.cls :: Nil
401       case tp: TypeRef =>
402         val sym = tp.symbol
403         if (sym.isClass) sym.asClass :: Nil else tp.superType.classSymbols: @tailrec
404       case tp: TypeProxy =>
405         tp.underlying.classSymbols: @tailrec
406       case AndType(l, r) =>
407         l.classSymbols union r.classSymbols
408       case OrType(l, r) =>
409         l.classSymbols intersect r.classSymbols // TODO does not conform to spec
410       case _ =>
411         Nil
412     }
413 
414     /** The term symbol associated with the type */
415     @tailrec final def termSymbol(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = this match {
416       case tp: TermRef => tp.symbol
417       case tp: TypeProxy => tp.underlying.termSymbol
418       case _ => NoSymbol
419     }
420 
421     /** The base classes of this type as determined by ClassDenotation
422      *  in linearization order, with the class itself as first element.
423      *  Inherited by all type proxies. Overridden for And and Or types.
424      *  `Nil` for all other types.
425      */
426     def baseClasses(implicit ctx: Context): List[ClassSymbol] = track("baseClasses") {
427       this match {
428         case tp: TypeProxy =>
429           tp.underlying.baseClasses
430         case tp: ClassInfo =>
431           tp.cls.baseClasses
432         case _ => Nil
433       }
434     }

438     /** The scope of all declarations of this type.
439      *  Defined by ClassInfo, inherited by type proxies.
440      *  Empty scope for all other types.
441      */
442     @tailrec final def decls(implicit ctx: Context): Scope = this match {
443       case tp: ClassInfo =>
444         tp.decls
445       case tp: TypeProxy =>
446         tp.underlying.decls: @tailrec
447       case _ =>
448         EmptyScope
449     }
450 
451     /** A denotation containing the declaration(s) in this type with the given name.
452      *  The result is either a SymDenotation or a MultiDenotation of SymDenotations.
453      *  The info(s) are the original symbol infos, no translation takes place.
454      */
455     final def decl(name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = track("decl") {
456       findDecl(name, EmptyFlags)
457     }
458 
459     /** A denotation containing the non-private declaration(s) in this type with the given name */
460     final def nonPrivateDecl(name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = track("nonPrivateDecl") {
461       findDecl(name, Private)
462     }
463 
464     /** A denotation containing the declaration(s) in this type with the given
465      *  name, as seen from prefix type `pre`. Declarations that have a flag
466      *  in `excluded` are omitted.
467      */
468     @tailrec final def findDecl(name: Name, excluded: FlagSet)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = this match {
469       case tp: ClassInfo =>
470         tp.decls.denotsNamed(name).filterExcluded(excluded).toDenot(NoPrefix)
471       case tp: TypeProxy =>
472         tp.underlying.findDecl(name, excluded)
473       case err: ErrorType =>
474         ctx.newErrorSymbol(classSymbol orElse defn.RootClass, name, err.msg)
475       case _ =>
476         NoDenotation
477     }
478 
479     /** The member of this type with the given name  */
480     final def member(name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = /*>|>*/ track("member") /*<|<*/ {
481       memberExcluding(name, EmptyFlags)
482     }
483 
484     /** The non-private member of this type with the given name. */
485     final def nonPrivateMember(name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = track("nonPrivateMember") {
486       memberExcluding(name, Flags.Private)
487     }
488 
489     final def memberExcluding(name: Name, excluding: FlagSet)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = {
490       // We need a valid prefix for `asSeenFrom`
491       val pre = this match {
492         case tp: ClassInfo => tp.appliedRef
493         case _ => widenIfUnstable
494       }
495       findMember(name, pre, excluding)
496     }
497 
498     /** Find member of this type with given name and
499      *  produce a denotation that contains the type of the member
500      *  as seen from given prefix `pre`. Exclude all members that have
501      *  flags in `excluded` from consideration.
502      */
503     final def findMember(name: Name, pre: Type, excluded: FlagSet)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = {
504       @tailrec def go(tp: Type): Denotation = tp match {
505         case tp: TermRef =>
506           go (tp.underlying match {
507             case mt: MethodType
508             if mt.paramInfos.isEmpty && (tp.symbol is Stable) => mt.resultType
509             case tp1 => tp1
510           })
511         case tp: TypeRef =>
512           tp.denot.findMember(name, pre, excluded)
513         case tp: AppliedType =>
514           goApplied(tp)
515         case tp: ThisType =>
516           goThis(tp)
517         case tp: RefinedType =>
518           if (name eq tp.refinedName) goRefined(tp) else go(tp.parent)
519         case tp: RecType =>
520           goRec(tp)
521         case tp: TypeParamRef =>
522           goParam(tp)
523         case tp: SuperType =>
524           goSuper(tp)
525         case tp: TypeProxy =>
526           go(tp.underlying)
527         case tp: ClassInfo =>
528           tp.cls.findMember(name, pre, excluded)
529         case AndType(l, r) =>
530           goAnd(l, r)
531         case tp: OrType =>
532           // we need to keep the invariant that `pre <: tp`. Branch `union-types-narrow-prefix`
533           // achieved that by narrowing `pre` to each alternative, but it led to merge errors in
534           // lots of places. The present strategy is instead of widen `tp` using `join` to be a
535           // supertype of `pre`.
536           go(tp.join)
537         case tp: JavaArrayType =>
538           defn.ObjectType.findMember(name, pre, excluded)
539         case err: ErrorType =>
540           ctx.newErrorSymbol(pre.classSymbol orElse defn.RootClass, name, err.msg)
541         case _ =>
542           NoDenotation
543       }
544       def goRec(tp: RecType) =
545         if (tp.parent == null) NoDenotation
546         else {
547           //println(s"find member $pre . $name in $tp")
548 
549           // We have to be careful because we might open the same (wrt eq) recursive type
550           // twice during findMember which risks picking the wrong prefix in the `substRecThis(rt, pre)`
551           // call below. To avoid this problem we do a defensive copy of the recursive
552           // type first. But if we do this always we risk being inefficient and we ran into
553           // stackoverflows when compiling pos/hk.scala under the refinement encoding
554           // of hk-types. So we only do a copy if the type
555           // is visited again in a recursive call to `findMember`, as tracked by `tp.opened`.
556           // Furthermore, if this happens we mark the original recursive type with `openedTwice`
557           // which means that we always defensively copy the type in the future. This second
558           // measure is necessary because findMember calls might be cached, so do not
559           // necessarily appear in nested order.
560           // Without the defensive copy, Typer.scala fails to compile at the line
561           //
562           //      untpd.rename(lhsCore, setterName).withType(setterType), WildcardType)
563           //
564           // because the subtype check
565           //
566           //      ThisTree[Untyped]#ThisTree[Typed] <: Tree[Typed]
567           //
568           // fails (in fact it thinks the underlying type of the LHS is `Tree[Untyped]`.)
569           //
570           // Without the `openedTwice` trick, Typer.scala fails to Ycheck
571           // at phase resolveSuper.
572           val rt =
573             if (tp.opened) { // defensive copy
574               tp.openedTwice = true
575               RecType(rt => tp.parent.substRecThis(tp, rt.recThis))
576             } else tp
577           rt.opened = true
578           try go(rt.parent).mapInfo(_.substRecThis(rt, pre))
579           finally {
580             if (!rt.openedTwice) rt.opened = false
581           }
582         }
583 
584       def goRefined(tp: RefinedType) = {
585         val pdenot = go(tp.parent)
586         val rinfo = tp.refinedInfo
587         if (name.isTypeName) { // simplified case that runs more efficiently
588           val jointInfo =
589             if (rinfo.isAlias) rinfo
590             else if (pdenot.info.isAlias) pdenot.info
591             else if (ctx.pendingMemberSearches.contains(name)) pdenot.info safe_& rinfo
592             else pdenot.info recoverable_& rinfo
593           pdenot.asSingleDenotation.derivedSingleDenotation(pdenot.symbol, jointInfo)
594         } else {
595           pdenot & (
596             new JointRefDenotation(NoSymbol, rinfo, Period.allInRun(ctx.runId)),
597             pre,
598             safeIntersection = ctx.pendingMemberSearches.contains(name))
599         }
600       }
601 
602       def goApplied(tp: AppliedType) = tp.tycon match {
603         case tl: HKTypeLambda =>
604           go(tl.resType).mapInfo(info =>
605             tl.derivedLambdaAbstraction(tl.paramNames, tl.paramInfos, info).appliedTo(tp.args))
606         case tc: TypeRef if tc.symbol.isClass =>
607           go(tc)
608         case _ =>
609           go(tp.superType)
610       }
611 
612       def goThis(tp: ThisType) = {
613         val d = go(tp.underlying)
614         if (d.exists) d
615         else
616           // There is a special case to handle:
617           //   trait Super { this: Sub => private class Inner {} println(this.Inner) }
618           //   class Sub extends Super
619           // When resolving Super.this.Inner, the normal logic goes to the self type and
620           // looks for Inner from there. But this fails because Inner is private.
621           // We fix the problem by having the following fallback case, which links up the
622           // member in Super instead of Sub.
623           // As an example of this in the wild, see
624           // loadClassWithPrivateInnerAndSubSelf in ShowClassTests
625           go(tp.cls.typeRef) orElse d
626       }
627       def goParam(tp: TypeParamRef) = {
628         val next = tp.underlying
629         ctx.typerState.constraint.entry(tp) match {
630           case bounds: TypeBounds if bounds ne next =>
631             ctx.typerState.ephemeral = true
632             go(bounds.hi)
633           case _ =>
634             go(next)
635         }
636       }
637       def goSuper(tp: SuperType) = go(tp.underlying) match {
638         case d: JointRefDenotation =>
639           typr.println(i"redirecting super.$name from $tp to ${d.symbol.showLocated}")
640           new UniqueRefDenotation(d.symbol, tp.memberInfo(d.symbol), d.validFor)
641         case d => d
642       }
643       def goAnd(l: Type, r: Type) = {
644         go(l) & (go(r), pre, safeIntersection = ctx.pendingMemberSearches.contains(name))
645       }
646 
647       val recCount = ctx.findMemberCount
648       if (recCount >= Config.LogPendingFindMemberThreshold) {
649         if (ctx.property(TypeOps.findMemberLimit).isDefined &&
650             ctx.findMemberCount > Config.PendingFindMemberLimit)
651           return NoDenotation
652         ctx.pendingMemberSearches = name :: ctx.pendingMemberSearches
653       }
654       ctx.findMemberCount = recCount + 1
655       //assert(ctx.findMemberCount < 20)
656       try go(this)
657       catch {
658         case ex: Throwable =>
659           core.println(i"findMember exception for $this member $name, pre = $pre")
660           throw ex // DEBUG
661       }
662       finally {
663         if (recCount >= Config.LogPendingFindMemberThreshold)
664           ctx.pendingMemberSearches = ctx.pendingMemberSearches.tail
665         ctx.findMemberCount = recCount
666       }
667     }
668 
669     /** The set of names of members of this type that pass the given name filter
670      *  when seen as members of `pre`. More precisely, these are all
671      *  of members `name` such that `keepOnly(pre, name)` is `true`.
672      *  @note: OK to use a Set[Name] here because Name hashcodes are replayable,
673      *         hence the Set will always give the same names in the same order.
674      */
675     final def memberNames(keepOnly: NameFilter, pre: Type = this)(implicit ctx: Context): Set[Name] = this match {
676       case tp: ClassInfo =>
677         tp.cls.memberNames(keepOnly) filter (keepOnly(pre, _))
678       case tp: RefinedType =>
679         val ns = tp.parent.memberNames(keepOnly, pre)
680         if (keepOnly(pre, tp.refinedName)) ns + tp.refinedName else ns
681       case tp: TypeProxy =>
682         tp.underlying.memberNames(keepOnly, pre): @tailrec
683       case tp: AndType =>
684         tp.tp1.memberNames(keepOnly, pre) | tp.tp2.memberNames(keepOnly, pre)
685       case tp: OrType =>
686         tp.tp1.memberNames(keepOnly, pre) & tp.tp2.memberNames(keepOnly, pre)
687       case _ =>
688         Set()
689     }
690 
691     def memberDenots(keepOnly: NameFilter, f: (Name, mutable.Buffer[SingleDenotation]) => Unit)(implicit ctx: Context): Seq[SingleDenotation] = {
692       val buf = mutable.ArrayBuffer[SingleDenotation]()
693       for (name <- memberNames(keepOnly)) f(name, buf)
694       buf
695     }
696 
697     /** The set of abstract term members of this type. */
698     final def abstractTermMembers(implicit ctx: Context): Seq[SingleDenotation] = track("abstractTermMembers") {
699       memberDenots(abstractTermNameFilter,
700           (name, buf) => buf ++= nonPrivateMember(name).altsWith(_ is Deferred))
701     }
702 
703     /** The set of abstract type members of this type. */
704     final def abstractTypeMembers(implicit ctx: Context): Seq[SingleDenotation] = track("abstractTypeMembers") {
705       memberDenots(abstractTypeNameFilter,
706           (name, buf) => buf += nonPrivateMember(name).asSingleDenotation)
707     }
708 
709     /** The set of abstract type members of this type. */
710     final def nonClassTypeMembers(implicit ctx: Context): Seq[SingleDenotation] = track("nonClassTypeMembers") {
711       memberDenots(nonClassTypeNameFilter,
712           (name, buf) => buf += member(name).asSingleDenotation)
713     }
714 
715     /** The set of type alias members of this type */
716     final def typeAliasMembers(implicit ctx: Context): Seq[SingleDenotation] = track("typeAlias") {
717       memberDenots(typeAliasNameFilter,
718           (name, buf) => buf += member(name).asSingleDenotation)
719     }
720 
721     /** The set of type members of this type */
722     final def typeMembers(implicit ctx: Context): Seq[SingleDenotation] = track("typeMembers") {
723       memberDenots(typeNameFilter,
724           (name, buf) => buf += member(name).asSingleDenotation)
725     }
726 
727     /** The set of implicit members of this type */
728     final def implicitMembers(implicit ctx: Context): List[TermRef] = track("implicitMembers") {
729       memberDenots(implicitFilter,
730           (name, buf) => buf ++= member(name).altsWith(_ is Implicit))
731         .toList.map(d => TermRef(this, d.symbol.asTerm))
732     }
733 
734     /** The set of member classes of this type */
735     final def memberClasses(implicit ctx: Context): Seq[SingleDenotation] = track("implicitMembers") {
736       memberDenots(typeNameFilter,
737         (name, buf) => buf ++= member(name).altsWith(x => x.isClass))
738     }
739 
740     final def fields(implicit ctx: Context): Seq[SingleDenotation] = track("fields") {
741       memberDenots(fieldFilter,
742         (name, buf) => buf ++= member(name).altsWith(x => !x.is(Method)))
743     }
744 
745     /** The set of members of this type having at least one of `requiredFlags` but none of `excludedFlags` set */
746     final def membersBasedOnFlags(requiredFlags: FlagSet, excludedFlags: FlagSet)(implicit ctx: Context): Seq[SingleDenotation] = track("implicitMembers") {
747       memberDenots(takeAllFilter,
748         (name, buf) => buf ++= memberExcluding(name, excludedFlags).altsWith(x => x.is(requiredFlags)))
749     }
750 
751     /** The info of `sym`, seen as a member of this type. */
752     final def memberInfo(sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
753       sym.info.asSeenFrom(this, sym.owner)
754 
755     /** This type seen as if it were the type of a member of prefix type `pre`
756      *  declared in class `cls`.
757      */
758     final def asSeenFrom(pre: Type, cls: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = track("asSeenFrom") {
759       if (!cls.membersNeedAsSeenFrom(pre)) this
760       else ctx.asSeenFrom(this, pre, cls)
761     }

763 // ----- Subtype-related --------------------------------------------
