765     /** Is this type a subtype of that type? */
766     final def <:<(that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = track("<:<") {
767       ctx.typeComparer.topLevelSubType(this, that)
768     }
769 
770     /** Is this type a subtype of that type? */
771     final def frozen_<:<(that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = track("frozen_<:<") {
772       ctx.typeComparer.isSubTypeWhenFrozen(this, that)
773     }
774 
775     /** Is this type the same as that type?
776      *  This is the case iff `this <:< that` and `that <:< this`.
777      */
778     final def =:=(that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = track("=:=") {
779       ctx.typeComparer.isSameType(this, that)
780     }
781 
782     /** Is this type a primitive value type which can be widened to the primitive value type `that`? */
783     def isValueSubType(that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = widen match {
784       case self: TypeRef if self.symbol.isPrimitiveValueClass =>
785         that.widenExpr match {
786           case that: TypeRef if that.symbol.isPrimitiveValueClass =>
787             defn.isValueSubClass(self.symbol, that.symbol)
788           case _ =>
789             false
790         }
791       case _ =>
792         false
793     }
794 
795     def relaxed_<:<(that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) =
796       (this <:< that) || (this isValueSubType that)
797 
798     /** Is this type a legal type for member `sym1` that overrides another
799      *  member `sym2` of type `that`? This is the same as `<:<`, except that
800      *  if `matchLoosely` evaluates to true the types `=> T` and `()T` are seen
801      *  as overriding each other.
802      */
803     final def overrides(that: Type, matchLoosely: => Boolean)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = {
804       def widenNullary(tp: Type) = tp match {
805         case tp @ MethodType(Nil) => tp.resultType
806         case _ => tp
807       }
808       ((this.widenExpr frozen_<:< that.widenExpr) ||
809         matchLoosely && {
810           val this1 = widenNullary(this)
811           val that1 = widenNullary(that)
812           ((this1 `ne` this) || (that1 `ne` that)) && this1.overrides(this1, matchLoosely = false)
813         }
814       )
815     }
816 
817     /** Is this type close enough to that type so that members
818      *  with the two types would override each other?
819      *  This means:
820      *    - Either both types are polytypes with the same number of
821      *      type parameters and their result types match after renaming
822      *      corresponding type parameters
823      *    - Or both types are method types with =:=-equivalent(*) parameter types
824      *      and matching result types after renaming corresponding parameter types
825      *      if the method types are dependent.
826      *    - Or both types are =:=-equivalent
827      *    - Or phase.erasedTypes is false, and neither type takes
828      *      term or type parameters.
829      *
830      *  (*) when matching with a Java method, we also regard Any and Object as equivalent
831      *      parameter types.
832      */
833     def matches(that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = track("matches") {
834       ctx.typeComparer.matchesType(this, that, relaxed = !ctx.phase.erasedTypes)
835     }
836 
837     /** This is the same as `matches` except that it also matches => T with T and
838      *  vice versa.
839      */
840     def matchesLoosely(that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
841       (this matches that) || {
842         val thisResult = this.widenExpr
843         val thatResult = that.widenExpr
844         (this eq thisResult) != (that eq thatResult) && (thisResult matchesLoosely thatResult)
845       }
846 
847     /** The basetype of this type with given class symbol, NoType if `base` is not a class. */
848     final def baseType(base: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = /*trace(s"$this baseType $base")*/ /*>|>*/ track("base type") /*<|<*/ {
849       base.denot match {
850         case classd: ClassDenotation => classd.baseTypeOf(this)
851         case _ => NoType
852       }
853     }
854 
855     def & (that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = track("&") {
856       ctx.typeComparer.glb(this, that)
857     }
858 
859     /** Safer version of `&`.
860      *
861      *  This version does not simplify the bounds of the intersection of
862      *  two TypeBounds. The simplification done by `&` requires subtyping checks
863      *  which may end up calling `&` again, in most cases this should be safe
864      *  but because of F-bounded types, this can result in an infinite loop
865      *  (which will be masked unless `-Yno-deep-subtypes` is enabled).
866      *  pos/i536 demonstrates that the infinite loop can also involve lower bounds.
867      */
868     def safe_& (that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = (this, that) match {
869       case (TypeBounds(lo1, hi1), TypeBounds(lo2, hi2)) => TypeBounds(OrType(lo1, lo2), AndType(hi1, hi2))
870       case _ => this & that
871     }
872 
873     /** `this & that`, but handle CyclicReferences by falling back to `safe_&`.
874      */
875     def recoverable_&(that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
876       try this & that
877       catch {
878         case ex: CyclicReference => this safe_& that
879           // A test case where this happens is tests/pos/i536.scala.
880           // The & causes a subtype check which calls baseTypeRef again with the same
881           // superclass.
882       }
883 
884     def | (that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = track("|") {
885       ctx.typeComparer.lub(this, that)
886     }
887 
888 // ----- Unwrapping types -----------------------------------------------
889 
890     /** Map a TypeVar to either its instance if it is instantiated, or its origin,
891      *  if not, until the result is no longer a TypeVar. Identity on all other types.
892      */
893     def stripTypeVar(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this
894 
895     /** Remove all AnnotatedTypes wrapping this type.
896       */
897     def stripAnnots(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this
898 
899     /** Strip PolyType prefix */
900     def stripPoly(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this match {
901       case tp: PolyType => tp.resType.stripPoly
902       case _ => this
903     }
904 
905     /** Widen from singleton type to its underlying non-singleton
906      *  base type by applying one or more `underlying` dereferences,
907      *  Also go from => T to T.
908      *  Identity for all other types. Example:
909      *
910      *  class Outer { class C ; val x: C }
911      *  def o: Outer
912      *  <o.x.type>.widen = o.C
913      */
914     final def widen(implicit ctx: Context): Type = widenSingleton match {
915       case tp: ExprType => tp.resultType.widen
916       case tp => tp
917     }
918 
919     /** Widen from singleton type to its underlying non-singleton
920      *  base type by applying one or more `underlying` dereferences.
921      */
922     final def widenSingleton(implicit ctx: Context): Type = stripTypeVar.stripAnnots match {
923       case tp: SingletonType if !tp.isOverloaded => tp.underlying.widenSingleton
924       case _ => this
925     }
926 
927     /** Widen from TermRef to its underlying non-termref
928      *  base type, while also skipping Expr types.
929      */
930     final def widenTermRefExpr(implicit ctx: Context): Type = stripTypeVar match {
931       case tp: TermRef if !tp.isOverloaded => tp.underlying.widenExpr.widenTermRefExpr
932       case _ => this
933     }
934 
935     /** Widen from ExprType type to its result type.
936      *  (Note: no stripTypeVar needed because TypeVar's can't refer to ExprTypes.)
937      */
938     final def widenExpr: Type = this match {
939       case tp: ExprType => tp.resType
940       case _ => this
941     }
942 
943     /** Widen type if it is unstable (i.e. an ExprType, or TermRef to unstable symbol */
944     final def widenIfUnstable(implicit ctx: Context): Type = stripTypeVar match {
945       case tp: ExprType => tp.resultType.widenIfUnstable
946       case tp: TermRef if !tp.symbol.isStable => tp.underlying.widenIfUnstable
947       case _ => this
948     }
949 
950     /** If this is a skolem, its underlying type, otherwise the type itself */
951     final def widenSkolem(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this match {
952       case tp: SkolemType => tp.underlying
953       case _ => this
954     }
955 
956     /** If this type contains embedded union types, replace them by their joins.
957      *  "Embedded" means: inside intersectons or recursive types, or in prefixes of refined types.
958      *  If an embedded union is found, we first try to simplify or eliminate it by
959      *  re-lubbing it while allowing type parameters to be constrained further.
960      *  Any remaining union types are replaced by their joins.
961      *
962 	   *  For instance, if `A` is an unconstrained type variable, then
963   	 *
964   	 * 	      ArrayBuffer[Int] | ArrayBuffer[A]
965   	 *
966      *  is approximated by constraining `A` to be =:= to `Int` and returning `ArrayBuffer[Int]`
967      *  instead of `ArrayBuffer[_ >: Int | A <: Int & A]`
968      */
969     def widenUnion(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this match {
970       case OrType(tp1, tp2) =>
971         ctx.typeComparer.lub(tp1.widenUnion, tp2.widenUnion, canConstrain = true) match {
972           case union: OrType => union.join
973           case res => res
974         }
975       case tp @ AndType(tp1, tp2) =>
976         tp derived_& (tp1.widenUnion, tp2.widenUnion)
977       case tp: RefinedType =>
978         tp.derivedRefinedType(tp.parent.widenUnion, tp.refinedName, tp.refinedInfo)
979       case tp: RecType =>
980         tp.rebind(tp.parent.widenUnion)
981       case _ =>
982         this
983     }
984 
985     private def dealias(keepAnnots: Boolean)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this match {
986       case tp: TypeRef =>
987         if (tp.symbol.isClass) tp
988         else tp.info match {
989           case TypeAlias(tp) => tp.dealias(keepAnnots): @tailrec
990           case _ => tp
991         }
992       case app @ AppliedType(tycon, args) =>
993         val tycon1 = tycon.dealias(keepAnnots)
994         if (tycon1 ne tycon) app.superType.dealias(keepAnnots): @tailrec
995         else this
996       case tp: TypeVar =>
997         val tp1 = tp.instanceOpt
998         if (tp1.exists) tp1.dealias(keepAnnots): @tailrec else tp
999       case tp: AnnotatedType =>
1000         val tp1 = tp.tpe.dealias(keepAnnots)
1001         if (keepAnnots) tp.derivedAnnotatedType(tp1, tp.annot) else tp1
1002       case tp: LazyRef =>
1003         tp.ref.dealias(keepAnnots): @tailrec
1004       case _ => this
1005     }
1006 
1007     /** Follow aliases and dereferences LazyRefs and instantiated TypeVars until type
1008      *  is no longer alias type, LazyRef, or instantiated type variable.
1009      *  Goes through annotated types and rewraps annotations on the result.
1010      */
1011     final def dealiasKeepAnnots(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1012       dealias(keepAnnots = true)
1013 
1014     /** Follow aliases and dereferences LazyRefs, annotated types and instantiated
1015      *  TypeVars until type is no longer alias type, annotated type, LazyRef,
1016      *  or instantiated type variable.
1017      */
1018     final def dealias(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1019       dealias(keepAnnots = false)
1020 
1021     /** Perform successive widenings and dealiasings until none can be applied anymore */
1022     @tailrec final def widenDealias(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
1023       val res = this.widen.dealias
1024       if (res eq this) res else res.widenDealias
1025     }
1026 
1027     /** Widen from constant type to its underlying non-constant
1028      *  base type.
1029      */
1030     final def deconst(implicit ctx: Context): Type = stripTypeVar match {
1031       case tp: ConstantType => tp.value.tpe
1032       case _ => this
1033     }
1034 
1035     /** Dealias, and if result is a dependent function type, drop the `apply` refinement. */
1036     final def dropDependentRefinement(implicit ctx: Context): Type = dealias match {
1037       case RefinedType(parent, nme.apply, _) => parent
1038       case tp => tp
1039     }
1040 
1041     /** The type constructor of an applied type, otherwise the type itself */
1042     final def typeConstructor(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this match {
1043       case AppliedType(tycon, _) => tycon
1044       case _ => this
1045     }
1046 
1047     /** If this is a (possibly aliased, annotated, and/or parameterized) reference to
1048      *  a class, the class type ref, otherwise NoType.
1049      *  @param  refinementOK   If `true` we also skip refinements.
1050      */
1051     def underlyingClassRef(refinementOK: Boolean)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = dealias match {
1052       case tp: TypeRef =>
1053         if (tp.symbol.isClass) tp
1054         else if (tp.symbol.isAliasType) tp.underlying.underlyingClassRef(refinementOK)
1055         else NoType
1056       case tp: AppliedType =>
1057         tp.superType.underlyingClassRef(refinementOK)
1058       case tp: AnnotatedType =>
1059         tp.underlying.underlyingClassRef(refinementOK)
1060       case tp: RefinedType =>
1061         if (refinementOK) tp.underlying.underlyingClassRef(refinementOK) else NoType
1062       case tp: RecType =>
1063         tp.underlying.underlyingClassRef(refinementOK)
1064       case _ =>
1065         NoType
1066     }
1067 
1068     /** The iterator of underlying types as long as type is a TypeProxy.
1069      *  Useful for diagnostics
1070      */
1071     def underlyingIterator(implicit ctx: Context): Iterator[Type] = new Iterator[Type] {
1072       var current = Type.this
1073       var hasNext = true
1074       def next = {
1075         val res = current
1076         hasNext = current.isInstanceOf[TypeProxy]
1077         if (hasNext) current = current.asInstanceOf[TypeProxy].underlying
1078         res
1079       }
1080     }
1081 
1082     /** A prefix-less refined this or a termRef to a new skolem symbol
1083      *  that has the given type as info.
1084      */
1085     def narrow(implicit ctx: Context): TermRef =
1086       TermRef(NoPrefix, ctx.newSkolem(this))
1087 
1088     /** Useful for diagnostics: The underlying type if this type is a type proxy,
1089      *  otherwise NoType
1090      */
1091     def underlyingIfProxy(implicit ctx: Context) = this match {
1092       case this1: TypeProxy => this1.underlying
1093       case _ => NoType
1094     }
1095 
1096     /** If this is a repeated type, its element type, otherwise the type itself */
1097     def repeatedToSingle(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this match {
1098       case tp @ ExprType(tp1) => tp.derivedExprType(tp1.repeatedToSingle)
1099       case _                  => if (isRepeatedParam) this.argTypesHi.head else this
1100     }
1101 
1102     /** If this is a FunProto or PolyProto, WildcardType, otherwise this. */
1103     def notApplied: Type = this
1104 
1105     // ----- Normalizing typerefs over refined types ----------------------------
1106 
1107     /** If this normalizes* to a refinement type that has a refinement for `name` (which might be followed
1108      *  by other refinements), and the refined info is a type alias, return the alias,
1109      *  otherwise return NoType. Used to reduce types of the form
1110      *
1111      *    P { ... type T = / += / -= U ... } # T
1112      *
1113      *  to just U. Does not perform the reduction if the resulting type would contain
1114      *  a reference to the "this" of the current refined type, except in the following situation
1115      *
1116      *  (1) The "this" reference can be avoided by following an alias. Example:
1117      *
1118      *      P { type T = String, type R = P{...}.T } # R  -->  String
1119      *
1120      *  (*) normalizes means: follow instantiated typevars and aliases.
1121      */
1122     def lookupRefined(name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
1123       @tailrec def loop(pre: Type): Type = pre.stripTypeVar match {
1124         case pre: RefinedType =>
1125           pre.refinedInfo match {
1126             case TypeAlias(alias) =>
1127               if (pre.refinedName ne name) loop(pre.parent) else alias
1128             case _ => loop(pre.parent)
1129           }
1130         case pre: RecType =>
1131           val candidate = pre.parent.lookupRefined(name)
1132           if (candidate.exists && !pre.isReferredToBy(candidate)) {
1133             //println(s"lookupRefined ${this.toString} . $name, pre: $pre ---> $candidate / ${candidate.toString}")
1134             candidate
1135           }
1136           else NoType
1137         case SkolemType(tp) =>
1138           loop(tp)
1139         case pre: WildcardType =>
1140           WildcardType
1141         case pre: TypeRef =>
1142           pre.info match {
1143             case TypeAlias(alias) => loop(alias)
1144             case _ => NoType
1145           }
1146         case _ =>
1147           NoType
1148       }
1149 
1150       loop(this)
1151     }
1152 
1153     /** The type <this . name> , reduced if possible */
1154     def select(name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1155       NamedType(this, name, member(name)).reduceProjection
1156 
1157     /** The type <this . name> with given denotation, reduced if possible. */
1158     def select(name: Name, denot: Denotation)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1159       NamedType(this, name, denot).reduceProjection
1160 
1161     /** The type <this . sym>, reduced if possible */
1162     def select(sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1163       NamedType(this, sym).reduceProjection
1164 
1165     def select(name: TermName)(implicit ctx: Context): TermRef =
1166       TermRef(this, name, member(name))
1167 
1168     def select(name: TermName, sig: Signature)(implicit ctx: Context): TermRef =
1169       TermRef(this, name, member(name).atSignature(sig, relaxed = !ctx.erasedTypes))
1170 
1171 // ----- Access to parts --------------------------------------------
1172 
1173     /** The normalized prefix of this type is:
1174      *  For an alias type, the normalized prefix of its alias
1175      *  For all other named type and class infos: the prefix.
1176      *  Inherited by all other type proxies.
1177      *  `NoType` for all other types.
1178      */
1179     @tailrec final def normalizedPrefix(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this match {
1180       case tp: NamedType =>
1181         if (tp.symbol.info.isAlias) tp.info.normalizedPrefix else tp.prefix
1182       case tp: ClassInfo =>
1183         tp.prefix
1184       case tp: TypeProxy =>
1185         tp.underlying.normalizedPrefix
1186       case _ =>
1187         NoType
1188     }
1189 
1190     /** The full parent types, including all type arguments */
1191     def parents(implicit ctx: Context): List[Type] = this match {
1192       case tp @ AppliedType(tycon, args) if tycon.typeSymbol.isClass =>
1193         tycon.parents.map(_.subst(tycon.typeSymbol.typeParams, args))
1194       case tp: TypeRef =>
1195         if (tp.info.isInstanceOf[TempClassInfo]) {
1196           tp.recomputeDenot()
1197           assert(!tp.info.isInstanceOf[TempClassInfo])
1198         }
1199         tp.info.parents
1200       case tp: TypeProxy =>
1201         tp.superType.parents
1202       case _ => Nil
1203     }
1204 
1205     /** The first parent of this type, AnyRef if list of parents is empty */
1206     def firstParent(implicit ctx: Context): Type = parents match {
1207       case p :: _ => p
1208       case _ => defn.AnyType
1209     }
1210 
1211     /** The parameter types of a PolyType or MethodType, Empty list for others */
1212     final def paramInfoss(implicit ctx: Context): List[List[Type]] = stripPoly match {
1213       case mt: MethodType => mt.paramInfos :: mt.resultType.paramInfoss
1214       case _ => Nil
1215     }
1216 
1217     /** The parameter names of a PolyType or MethodType, Empty list for others */
1218     final def paramNamess(implicit ctx: Context): List[List[TermName]] = stripPoly match {
1219       case mt: MethodType => mt.paramNames :: mt.resultType.paramNamess
1220       case _ => Nil
1221     }
1222 
1223 
1224     /** The parameter types in the first parameter section of a generic type or MethodType, Empty list for others */
1225     final def firstParamTypes(implicit ctx: Context): List[Type] = stripPoly match {
1226       case mt: MethodType => mt.paramInfos
1227       case _ => Nil
1228     }
1229 
1230     /** Is this either not a method at all, or a parameterless method? */
1231     final def isParameterless(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = stripPoly match {
1232       case mt: MethodType => false
1233       case _ => true
1234     }
1235 
1236     /** The resultType of a LambdaType, or ExprType, the type itself for others */
1237     def resultType(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this
1238 
1239     /** The final result type of a PolyType, MethodType, or ExprType, after skipping
1240      *  all parameter sections, the type itself for all others.
1241      */
1242     def finalResultType(implicit ctx: Context): Type = resultType.stripPoly match {
1243       case mt: MethodType => mt.resultType.finalResultType
1244       case _ => resultType
1245     }
1246 
1247     /** This type seen as a TypeBounds */
1248     final def bounds(implicit ctx: Context): TypeBounds = this match {
1249       case tp: TypeBounds => tp
1250       case ci: ClassInfo => TypeAlias(ci.appliedRef)
1251       case wc: WildcardType =>
1252         wc.optBounds match {
1253           case bounds: TypeBounds => bounds
1254           case NoType => TypeBounds.empty
1255         }
1256       case _ => TypeAlias(this)
1257     }
1258 
1259     /** The lower bound of a TypeBounds type, the type itself otherwise */
1260     def loBound = this match {
1261       case tp: TypeBounds => tp.lo
1262       case _ => this
1263     }
1264 
1265     /** The upper bound of a TypeBounds type, the type itself otherwise */
1266     def hiBound = this match {
1267       case tp: TypeBounds => tp.hi
1268       case _ => this
1269     }
1270 
1271     /** The type parameter with given `name`. This tries first `decls`
1272      *  in order not to provoke a cycle by forcing the info. If that yields
1273      *  no symbol it tries `member` as an alternative.
1274      */
1275     def typeParamNamed(name: TypeName)(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
1276       classSymbol.unforcedDecls.lookup(name) orElse member(name).symbol
1277 
1278     /** If this is a prototype with some ignored component, reveal one more
1279      *  layer of it. Otherwise the type itself.
1280      */
1281     def deepenProto(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this
1282 
1283 // ----- Substitutions -----------------------------------------------------
1284 
1285     /** Substitute all types that refer in their symbol attribute to
1286      *  one of the symbols in `from` by the corresponding types in `to`.
1287      */
1288     final def subst(from: List[Symbol], to: List[Type])(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1289       if (from.isEmpty) this
1290       else {
1291         val from1 = from.tail
1292         if (from1.isEmpty) ctx.subst1(this, from.head, to.head, null)
1293         else {
1294           val from2 = from1.tail
1295           if (from2.isEmpty) ctx.subst2(this, from.head, to.head, from1.head, to.tail.head, null)
1296           else ctx.subst(this, from, to, null)
1297         }
1298       }
1299 
1300     /** Same as `subst` but follows aliases as a fallback. When faced with a reference
1301      *  to an alias type, where normal substitution does not yield a new type, the
1302      *  substitution is instead applied to the alias. If that yields a new type,
1303      *  this type is returned, otherwise the original type (not the alias) is returned.
1304      *  A use case for this method is if one wants to substitute the type parameters
1305      *  of a class and also wants to substitute any parameter accessors that alias
1306      *  the type parameters.
1307      */
1308     final def substDealias(from: List[Symbol], to: List[Type])(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1309       ctx.substDealias(this, from, to, null)
1310 
1311     /** Substitute all types of the form `TypeParamRef(from, N)` by
1312      *  `TypeParamRef(to, N)`.
1313      */
1314     final def subst(from: BindingType, to: BindingType)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1315       ctx.subst(this, from, to, null)
1316 
1317     /** Substitute all occurrences of `This(cls)` by `tp` */
1318     final def substThis(cls: ClassSymbol, tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1319       ctx.substThis(this, cls, tp, null)
1320 
1321     /** As substThis, but only is class is a static owner (i.e. a globally accessible object) */
1322     final def substThisUnlessStatic(cls: ClassSymbol, tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1323       if (cls.isStaticOwner) this else ctx.substThis(this, cls, tp, null)
1324 
1325     /** Substitute all occurrences of `RecThis(binder)` by `tp` */
1326     final def substRecThis(binder: RecType, tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1327       ctx.substRecThis(this, binder, tp, null)
1328 
1329     /** Substitute a bound type by some other type */
1330     final def substParam(from: ParamRef, to: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1331       ctx.substParam(this, from, to, null)
1332 
1333     /** Substitute bound types by some other types */
1334     final def substParams(from: BindingType, to: List[Type])(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1335       ctx.substParams(this, from, to, null)
1336 
1337     /** Substitute all occurrences of symbols in `from` by references to corresponding symbols in `to`
1338      */
1339     final def substSym(from: List[Symbol], to: List[Symbol])(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1340       ctx.substSym(this, from, to, null)
1341 
1342 // ----- misc -----------------------------------------------------------
1343 
1344     /** Turn type into a function type.
1345      *  @pre this is a method type without parameter dependencies.
1346      *  @param dropLast  The number of trailing parameters that should be dropped
1347      *                   when forming the function type.
1348      */
1349     def toFunctionType(dropLast: Int = 0)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this match {
1350       case mt: MethodType if !mt.isParamDependent =>
1351         val formals1 = if (dropLast == 0) mt.paramInfos else mt.paramInfos dropRight dropLast
1352         val funType = defn.FunctionOf(
1353           formals1 mapConserve (_.underlyingIfRepeated(mt.isJavaMethod)),
1354           mt.nonDependentResultApprox, mt.isImplicitMethod && !ctx.erasedTypes)
1355         if (mt.isDependent) RefinedType(funType, nme.apply, mt)
1356         else funType
1357     }
1358 
1359     /** The signature of this type. This is by default NotAMethod,
1360      *  but is overridden for PolyTypes, MethodTypes, and TermRef types.
1361      *  (the reason why we deviate from the "final-method-with-pattern-match-in-base-class"
1362      *   pattern is that method signatures use caching, so encapsulation
1363      *   is improved using an OO scheme).
1364      */
1365     def signature(implicit ctx: Context): Signature = Signature.NotAMethod
1366 
1367     def annotatedToRepeated(implicit ctx: Context): Type = this match {
1368       case tp @ ExprType(tp1) => tp.derivedExprType(tp1.annotatedToRepeated)
1369       case AnnotatedType(tp, annot) if annot matches defn.RepeatedAnnot =>
1370         val typeSym = tp.typeSymbol.asClass
1371         assert(typeSym == defn.SeqClass || typeSym == defn.ArrayClass)
1372         tp.translateParameterized(typeSym, defn.RepeatedParamClass)
1373       case _ => this
1374     }
1375 
1376     /** Convert to text */
1377     def toText(printer: Printer): Text = printer.toText(this)
1378 
1379     /** Utility method to show the underlying type of a TypeProxy chain together
1380      *  with the proxy type itself.
1381      */
1382     def showWithUnderlying(n: Int = 1)(implicit ctx: Context): String = this match {
1383       case tp: TypeProxy if n > 0 => s"$show with underlying ${tp.underlying.showWithUnderlying(n - 1)}"
1384       case _ => show
1385     }
1386 
1387     /** A simplified version of this type which is equivalent wrt =:= to this type.
1388      *  This applies a typemap to the type which (as all typemaps) follows type
1389      *  variable instances and reduces typerefs over refined types. It also
1390      *  re-evaluates all occurrences of And/OrType with &/| because
1391      *  what was a union or intersection of type variables might be a simpler type
1392      *  after the type variables are instantiated. Finally, it
1393      *  maps poly params in the current constraint set back to their type vars.
1394      */
1395     def simplified(implicit ctx: Context) = ctx.simplify(this, null)
1396 
1397     /** customized hash code of this type.
1398      *  NotCached for uncached types. Cached types
1399      *  compute hash and use it as the type's hashCode.
1400      */
1401     def hash: Int
1402 
1403     /** Equality used for hash-consing; uses `eq` on all recursive invocations.
1404      */
1405     def eql(that: Type): Boolean = this.equals(that)
1406 
1407   } // end Type
1408 
1409 // ----- Type categories ----------------------------------------------
1410 
1411   /** A marker trait for cached types */
1412   trait CachedType extends Type
1413 
1414   /** A marker trait for type proxies.
1415    *  Each implementation is expected to redefine the `underlying` method.
1416    */
1417   abstract class TypeProxy extends Type {
1418 
1419     /** The type to which this proxy forwards operations. */
1420     def underlying(implicit ctx: Context): Type
1421 
1422     /** The closest supertype of this type. This is the same as `underlying`,
1423      *  except that
1424      *    - instead of a TyperBounds type it returns its upper bound, and
1425      *    - for applied types it returns the upper bound of the constructor re-applied to the arguments.
1426      */
1427     def superType(implicit ctx: Context): Type = underlying match {
1428       case TypeBounds(_, hi) => hi
1429       case st => st
1430     }
1431   }
1432 
1433   // Every type has to inherit one of the following four abstract type classes.,
1434   // which determine whether the type is cached, and whether
1435   // it is a proxy of some other type. The duplication in their methods
1436   // is for efficiency.
1437 
1438   /**  Instances of this class are cached and are not proxies. */
1439   abstract class CachedGroundType extends Type with CachedType {
1440     private[this] var myHash = HashUnknown
1441     final def hash = {
1442       if (myHash == HashUnknown) {
1443         myHash = computeHash
1444         assert(myHash != HashUnknown)
1445       }
1446       myHash
1447     }
1448     override final def hashCode =
1449       if (hash == NotCached) System.identityHashCode(this) else hash
1450     def computeHash: Int
1451   }
1452 
1453   /**  Instances of this class are cached and are proxies. */
1454   abstract class CachedProxyType extends TypeProxy with CachedType {
1455     protected[this] var myHash = HashUnknown
1456     final def hash = {
1457       if (myHash == HashUnknown) {
1458         myHash = computeHash
1459         assert(myHash != HashUnknown)
1460       }
1461       myHash
1462     }
1463     override final def hashCode =
1464       if (hash == NotCached) System.identityHashCode(this) else hash
1465     def computeHash: Int
1466   }
1467 
1468   /**  Instances of this class are uncached and are not proxies. */
1469   abstract class UncachedGroundType extends Type {
1470     final def hash = NotCached
1471     if (monitored) {
1472       record(s"uncachable")
1473       record(s"uncachable: $getClass")
1474     }
1475   }
1476 
1477   /**  Instances of this class are uncached and are proxies. */
1478   abstract class UncachedProxyType extends TypeProxy {
1479     final def hash = NotCached
1480     if (monitored) {
1481       record(s"uncachable")
1482       record(s"uncachable: $getClass")
1483     }
1484   }
1485 
1486   /** A marker trait for types that apply only to type symbols */
1487   trait TypeType extends Type
1488 
1489   /** A marker trait for types that apply only to term symbols or that
1490    *  represent higher-kinded types.
1491    */
1492   trait TermType extends Type
1493 
1494   /** A marker trait for types that can be types of values or prototypes of value types */
1495   trait ValueTypeOrProto extends TermType
1496 
1497   /** A marker trait for types that can be types of values or wildcards */
1498   trait ValueTypeOrWildcard extends TermType
1499 
1500   /** A marker trait for types that can be types of values or that are higher-kinded  */
1501   trait ValueType extends ValueTypeOrProto with ValueTypeOrWildcard
1502 
1503   /** A marker trait for types that are guaranteed to contain only a
1504    *  single non-null value (they might contain null in addition).
1505    */
1506   trait SingletonType extends TypeProxy with ValueType {
1507     def isOverloaded(implicit ctx: Context) = false
1508   }
1509 
1510   /** A marker trait for types that bind other types that refer to them.
1511    *  Instances are: LambdaType, RecType.
1512    */
1513   trait BindingType extends Type
1514 
1515   /** A trait for proto-types, used as expected types in typer */
1516   trait ProtoType extends Type {
1517     def isMatchedBy(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean
1518     def fold[T](x: T, ta: TypeAccumulator[T])(implicit ctx: Context): T
1519     def map(tm: TypeMap)(implicit ctx: Context): ProtoType
1520   }
1521 
1522   /** Implementations of this trait cache the results of `narrow`. */
1523   trait NarrowCached extends Type {
1524     private[this] var myNarrow: TermRef = null
1525     override def narrow(implicit ctx: Context): TermRef = {
1526       if (myNarrow eq null) myNarrow = super.narrow
1527       myNarrow
1528     }
1529   }
1530 
1531 // --- NamedTypes ------------------------------------------------------------------
1532 
1533   abstract class NamedType extends CachedProxyType with ValueType { self =>
1534 
1535     type ThisType >: this.type <: NamedType
1536     type ThisName <: Name
1537 
1538     val prefix: Type
1539     def designator: Designator
1540     protected def designator_=(d: Designator): Unit
1541 
1542     assert(prefix.isValueType || (prefix eq NoPrefix), s"invalid prefix $prefix")
1543 
1544     private[this] var myName: Name = null
1545     private[this] var mySig: Signature = null
1546     private[this] var lastDenotation: Denotation = null
1547     private[this] var lastSymbol: Symbol = null
1548     private[this] var checkedPeriod: Period = Nowhere
1549 
1550     // Invariants:
1551     // (1) checkedPeriod != Nowhere  =>  lastDenotation != null
1552     // (2) lastDenotation != null    =>  lastSymbol != null
1553 
1554     def isType = isInstanceOf[TypeRef]
1555     def isTerm = isInstanceOf[TermRef]
1556 
1557     /** If designator is a name, this name. Otherwise, the original name
1558      *  of the designator symbol.
1559      */
1560     final def name(implicit ctx: Context): ThisName = {
1561       if (myName == null) myName = computeName
1562       myName.asInstanceOf[ThisName]
1563     }
1564 
1565     private def computeName: Name = designator match {
1566       case name: Name => name
1567       case sym: Symbol => sym.originDenotation.name
1568     }
1569 
1570     /** The signature of the last known denotation, or if there is none, the
1571      *  signature of the symbol
1572      */
1573     final override def signature(implicit ctx: Context): Signature = {
1574       if (mySig == null) mySig = computeSignature
1575       mySig
1576     }
1577 
1578     def computeSignature(implicit ctx: Context): Signature = {
1579       val lastd = lastDenotation
1580       if (lastd != null) lastd.signature
1581       else symbol.asSeenFrom(prefix).signature
1582     }
1583 
1584     /** The signature of the current denotation if it is known without forcing.
1585      *  Otherwise the signature of the current symbol if it is known without forcing.
1586      *  Otherwise NotAMethod.
1587      */
1588     private def currentSignature(implicit ctx: Context): Signature =
1589       if (mySig != null) mySig
1590       else {
1591         val lastd = lastDenotation
1592         if (lastd != null) lastd.signature
1593         else {
1594           val sym = currentSymbol
1595           if (sym.exists) sym.asSeenFrom(prefix).signature
1596           else Signature.NotAMethod
1597         }
1598       }
1599 
1600     final def symbol(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
1601       if (checkedPeriod == ctx.period) lastSymbol else computeSymbol
1602 
1603     private def computeSymbol(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol =
1604       designator match {
1605         case sym: Symbol =>
1606           if (sym.isValidInCurrentRun) sym else denot.symbol
1607         case name =>
1608           (if (denotationIsCurrent) lastDenotation else denot).symbol
1609       }
1610 
1611     /** There is a denotation computed which is valid (somewhere in) the
1612      *  current run.
1613      */
1614     def denotationIsCurrent(implicit ctx: Context) =
1615       lastDenotation != null && lastDenotation.validFor.runId == ctx.runId
1616 
1617     /** If the reference is symbolic or the denotation is current, its symbol, otherwise NoDenotation.
1618      *
1619      *  Note: This operation does not force the denotation, and is therefore
1620      *  timing dependent. It should only be used if the outcome of the
1621      *  essential computation does not depend on the symbol being present or not.
1622      *  It's currently used to take an optimized path in substituters and
1623      *  type accumulators, as well as to be safe in diagnostic printing.
1624      *  Normally, it's better to use `symbol`, not `currentSymbol`.
1625      */
1626     final def currentSymbol(implicit ctx: Context) = designator match {
1627       case sym: Symbol => sym
1628       case _ => if (denotationIsCurrent) lastDenotation.symbol else NoSymbol
1629     }
1630 
1631     /** Retrieves currently valid symbol without necessarily updating denotation.
1632      *  Assumes that symbols do not change between periods in the same run.
1633      *  Used to get the class underlying a ThisType.
1634      */
1635     private[Types] def stableInRunSymbol(implicit ctx: Context): Symbol = {
1636       if (checkedPeriod.runId == ctx.runId) lastSymbol
1637       else symbol
1638     }
1639 
1640     def info(implicit ctx: Context): Type = denot.info
1641 
1642     /** The denotation currently denoted by this type */
1643     final def denot(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = {
1644       val now = ctx.period
1645       val lastd = lastDenotation
1646       if (checkedPeriod == now) lastd else denotAt(lastd, now)
1647     }
1648 
1649     /** A first fall back to do a somewhat more expensive calculation in case the first
1650      *  attempt in `denot` does not yield a denotation.
1651      */
1652     private def denotAt(lastd: Denotation, now: Period)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = {
1653       if (lastd != null && (lastd.validFor contains now)) {
1654         checkedPeriod = now
1655         lastd
1656       }
1657       else computeDenot
1658     }
1659 
1660     private def computeDenot(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = {
1661 
1662       def finish(d: Denotation) = {
1663         if (ctx.typerState.ephemeral)
1664           record("ephemeral cache miss: memberDenot")
1665         else if (d.exists)
1666           // Avoid storing NoDenotations in the cache - we will not be able to recover from
1667           // them. The situation might arise that a type has NoDenotation in some later
1668           // phase but a defined denotation earlier (e.g. a TypeRef to an abstract type
1669           // is undefined after erasure.) We need to be able to do time travel back and
1670           // forth also in these cases.
1671           setDenot(d)
1672         d
1673       }
1674 
1675       def fromDesignator = designator match {
1676         case name: Name =>
1677           val sym = lastSymbol
1678           val allowPrivate = sym == null || (sym == NoSymbol) || sym.lastKnownDenotation.flagsUNSAFE.is(Private)
1679           finish(memberDenot(name, allowPrivate))
1680         case sym: Symbol =>
1681           val symd = sym.lastKnownDenotation
1682           if (symd.validFor.runId != ctx.runId && !ctx.stillValid(symd))
1683             finish(memberDenot(symd.initial.name, allowPrivate = false))
1684           else if (prefix.isArgPrefixOf(symd))
1685             finish(argDenot(sym.asType))
1686           else if (infoDependsOnPrefix(symd, prefix))
1687             finish(memberDenot(symd.initial.name, allowPrivate = symd.is(Private)))
1688           else
1689             finish(symd.current)
1690       }
1691 
1692       val savedEphemeral = ctx.typerState.ephemeral
1693       ctx.typerState.ephemeral = false
1694       try
1695         lastDenotation match {
1696           case lastd0: SingleDenotation =>
1697             val lastd = lastd0.skipRemoved
1698             if (lastd.validFor.runId == ctx.runId) finish(lastd.current)
1699             else lastd match {
1700               case lastd: SymDenotation =>
1701                 if (ctx.stillValid(lastd)) finish(lastd.current)
1702                 else finish(memberDenot(lastd.initial.name, allowPrivate = false))
1703               case _ =>
1704                 fromDesignator
1705             }
1706           case _ => fromDesignator
1707         }
1708       finally ctx.typerState.ephemeral |= savedEphemeral
1709     }
1710 
1711     private def disambiguate(d: Denotation)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation =
1712       disambiguate(d, currentSignature)
1713 
1714     private def disambiguate(d: Denotation, sig: Signature)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation =
1715       if (sig != null)
1716         d.atSignature(sig, relaxed = !ctx.erasedTypes) match {
1717           case d1: SingleDenotation => d1
1718           case d1 =>
1719             d1.atSignature(sig, relaxed = false) match {
1720               case d2: SingleDenotation => d2
1721               case d2 => d2.suchThat(currentSymbol.eq).orElse(d2)
1722             }
1723         }
1724       else d
1725 
1726     private def memberDenot(name: Name, allowPrivate: Boolean)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = {
1727       var d = memberDenot(prefix, name, allowPrivate)
1728       if (!d.exists && !allowPrivate && ctx.mode.is(Mode.Interactive))
1729         // In the IDE we might change a public symbol to private, and would still expect to find it.
1730         d = memberDenot(prefix, name, true)
1731       if (!d.exists && ctx.phaseId > FirstPhaseId && lastDenotation.isInstanceOf[SymDenotation])
1732         // name has changed; try load in earlier phase and make current
1733         d = memberDenot(name, allowPrivate)(ctx.withPhase(ctx.phaseId - 1)).current
1734       if (d.isOverloaded)
1735         d = disambiguate(d)
1736       d
1737     }
1738 
1739     private def memberDenot(prefix: Type, name: Name, allowPrivate: Boolean)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation =
1740       if (allowPrivate) prefix.member(name) else prefix.nonPrivateMember(name)
1741 
1742     private def argDenot(param: TypeSymbol)(implicit ctx: Context): Denotation = {
1743       val cls = param.owner
1744       val args = prefix.baseType(cls).argInfos
1745       val typeParams = cls.typeParams
1746 
1747       def concretize(arg: Type, tparam: TypeSymbol) = arg match {
1748         case arg: TypeBounds => TypeRef(prefix, tparam)
1749         case arg => arg
1750       }
1751       val concretized = args.zipWithConserve(typeParams)(concretize)
1752 
1753       def rebase(arg: Type) = arg.subst(typeParams, concretized)
1754 
1755       val idx = typeParams.indexOf(param)
1756 
1757       assert(args.nonEmpty,
1758       	i"""bad parameter reference $this at ${ctx.phase}
1759       	   |the parameter is ${param.showLocated} but the prefix $prefix
1760       	   |does not define any corresponding arguments.""")
1761 
1762       val argInfo = args(idx) match {
1763         case arg: TypeBounds =>
1764           val v = param.paramVariance
1765           val pbounds = param.paramInfo
1766           if (v > 0 && pbounds.loBound.dealias.isBottomType) TypeAlias(arg.hiBound & rebase(pbounds.hiBound))
1767           else if (v < 0 && pbounds.hiBound.dealias.isTopType) TypeAlias(arg.loBound | rebase(pbounds.loBound))
1768           else arg recoverable_& rebase(pbounds)
1769         case arg => TypeAlias(arg)
1770       }
1771       param.derivedSingleDenotation(param, argInfo)
1772     }
1773 
1774     /** Reload denotation by computing the member with the reference's name as seen
1775      *  from the reference's prefix.
1776      */
1777     def recomputeDenot()(implicit ctx: Context) =
1778       setDenot(memberDenot(name, allowPrivate = !symbol.exists || symbol.is(Private)))
1779 
1780     private def setDenot(denot: Denotation)(implicit ctx: Context): Unit = {
1781       if (ctx.isAfterTyper)
1782         assert(!denot.isOverloaded, this)
1783       if (Config.checkNoDoubleBindings)
1784         if (ctx.settings.YnoDoubleBindings.value)
1785           checkSymAssign(denot.symbol)
1786 
1787       lastDenotation = denot
1788       lastSymbol = denot.symbol
1789       checkedPeriod = ctx.period
1790       designator match {
1791         case sym: Symbol if designator ne lastSymbol =>
1792           designator = lastSymbol.asInstanceOf[Designator{ type ThisName = self.ThisName }]
1793         case _ =>
1794       }
1795       checkDenot()
1796     }
1797 
1798     private def checkDenot()(implicit ctx: Context) = {}
1799 
1800     private def checkSymAssign(sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context) = {
1801       def selfTypeOf(sym: Symbol) =
1802         if (sym.isClass) sym.asClass.givenSelfType else NoType
1803       assert(
1804         (lastSymbol eq sym)
1805         ||
1806         (lastSymbol eq null)
1807         ||
1808         !denotationIsCurrent
1809         ||
1810         lastSymbol.infoOrCompleter.isInstanceOf[ErrorType]
1811         ||
1812         sym.isPackageObject // package objects can be visited before we get around to index them
1813         ||
1814         sym.owner != lastSymbol.owner &&
1815           (sym.owner.derivesFrom(lastSymbol.owner)
1816            ||
1817            selfTypeOf(sym).derivesFrom(lastSymbol.owner)
1818            ||
1819            selfTypeOf(lastSymbol).derivesFrom(sym.owner)
1820           )
1821         ||
1822         sym == defn.AnyClass.primaryConstructor,
1823         s"""data race? overwriting $lastSymbol with $sym in type $this,
1824            |last sym id = ${lastSymbol.id}, new sym id = ${sym.id},
1825            |last owner = ${lastSymbol.owner}, new owner = ${sym.owner},
1826            |period = ${ctx.phase} at run ${ctx.runId}""")
1827     }
1828 
1829     /** A reference with the initial symbol in `symd` has an info that
1830      *  might depend on the given prefix.
1831      */
1832     private def infoDependsOnPrefix(symd: SymDenotation, prefix: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
1833       symd.maybeOwner.membersNeedAsSeenFrom(prefix) && !symd.is(NonMember)
1834 
1835     /** Is this a reference to a class or object member? */
1836     def isMemberRef(implicit ctx: Context) = designator match {
1837       case sym: Symbol => infoDependsOnPrefix(sym, prefix)
1838       case _ => true
1839     }
1840 
1841     /** (1) Reduce a type-ref `W # X` or `W { ... } # U`, where `W` is a wildcard type
1842      *  to an (unbounded) wildcard type.
1843      *
1844      *  (2) Reduce a type-ref `T { X = U; ... } # X`  to   `U`
1845      *  provided `U` does not refer with a RecThis to the
1846      *  refinement type `T { X = U; ... }`
1847      */
1848     def reduceProjection(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1849       if (isType) {
1850         val reduced = prefix.lookupRefined(name)
1851         if (reduced.exists) reduced else this
1852       }
1853       else this
1854 
1855     /** Guard against cycles that can arise if given `op`
1856      *  follows info. The problematic cases are a type alias to itself or
1857      *  bounded by itself or a val typed as itself:
1858      *
1859      *  type T <: T
1860      *  val x: x.type
1861      *
1862      *  These are errors but we have to make sure that operations do
1863      *  not loop before the error is detected.
1864      */
1865     final def controlled[T](op: => T)(implicit ctx: Context): T = try {
1866       ctx.underlyingRecursions += 1
1867       if (ctx.underlyingRecursions < Config.LogPendingUnderlyingThreshold)
1868         op
1869       else if (ctx.pendingUnderlying contains this)
1870         throw CyclicReference(symbol)
1871       else
1872         try {
1873           ctx.pendingUnderlying += this
1874           op
1875         } finally {
1876           ctx.pendingUnderlying -= this
1877         }
1878     } finally {
1879       ctx.underlyingRecursions -= 1
1880     }
1881 
1882     /** The argument corresponding to class type parameter `tparam` as seen from
1883      *  prefix `pre`.
1884      */
1885     def argForParam(pre: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
1886       val tparam = symbol
1887       val cls = tparam.owner
1888       val base = pre.baseType(cls)
1889       base match {
1890         case AppliedType(_, allArgs) =>
1891           var tparams = cls.typeParams
1892           var args = allArgs
1893           var idx = 0
1894           while (tparams.nonEmpty && args.nonEmpty) {
1895             if (tparams.head.eq(tparam))
1896               return args.head match {
1897                 case _: TypeBounds => TypeRef(pre, tparam)
1898                 case arg => arg
1899               }
1900             tparams = tparams.tail
1901             args = args.tail
1902             idx += 1
1903           }
1904           NoType
1905         case OrType(base1, base2) => argForParam(base1) | argForParam(base2)
1906         case AndType(base1, base2) => argForParam(base1) & argForParam(base2)
1907         case _ =>
1908           if (pre.termSymbol is Package) argForParam(pre.select(nme.PACKAGE))
1909           else if (pre.isBottomType) pre
1910           else NoType
1911       }
1912     }
1913 
1914     /** A selection of the same kind, but with potentially a different prefix.
1915      *  The following normalizations are performed for type selections T#A:
1916      *
1917      *     T#A --> B                if A is bound to an alias `= B` in T
1918      *
1919      *  If Config.splitProjections is set:
1920      *
1921      *     (S & T)#A --> S#A        if T does not have a member named A
1922      *               --> T#A        if S does not have a member named A
1923      *               --> S#A & T#A  otherwise
1924      *     (S | T)#A --> S#A | T#A
1925      */
1926     def derivedSelect(prefix: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
1927       if (prefix eq this.prefix) this
1928       else if (prefix.isBottomType) prefix
1929       else if (isType) {
1930         val res =
1931           if (currentSymbol.is(ClassTypeParam)) argForParam(prefix)
1932           else prefix.lookupRefined(name)
1933         if (res.exists) res
1934         else if (Config.splitProjections)
1935           prefix match {
1936             case prefix: AndType =>
1937               def isMissing(tp: Type) = tp match {
1938                 case tp: TypeRef => !tp.info.exists
1939                 case _ => false
1940               }
1941               val derived1 = derivedSelect(prefix.tp1)
1942               val derived2 = derivedSelect(prefix.tp2)
1943               return (
1944                 if (isMissing(derived1)) derived2
1945                 else if (isMissing(derived2)) derived1
1946                 else prefix.derivedAndType(derived1, derived2))
1947             case prefix: OrType =>
1948               val derived1 = derivedSelect(prefix.tp1)
1949               val derived2 = derivedSelect(prefix.tp2)
1950               return prefix.derivedOrType(derived1, derived2)
1951             case _ =>
1952               withPrefix(prefix)
1953           }
1954         else withPrefix(prefix)
1955       }
1956       else prefix match {
1957         case _: WildcardType => WildcardType
1958         case _ => withPrefix(prefix)
1959       }
1960 
1961     /** A reference like this one, but with the given symbol, if it exists */
1962     final def withSym(sym: Symbol)(implicit ctx: Context): ThisType =
1963       if ((designator ne sym) && sym.exists) NamedType(prefix, sym).asInstanceOf[ThisType]
1964       else this
1965 
1966     /** A reference like this one, but with the given denotation, if it exists.
1967      *  If the symbol of `denot` is the same as the current symbol, the denotation
1968      *  is re-used, otherwise a new one is created.
1969      */
1970     final def withDenot(denot: Denotation)(implicit ctx: Context): ThisType =
1971       if (denot.exists) {
1972         val adapted = withSym(denot.symbol)
1973         if (adapted ne this) adapted.withDenot(denot).asInstanceOf[ThisType]
1974         else {
1975           setDenot(denot)
1976           this
1977         }
1978       }
1979       else // don't assign NoDenotation, we might need to recover later. Test case is pos/avoid.scala.
1980         this
1981 
1982     /** A reference like this one, but with the given prefix. */
1983     final def withPrefix(prefix: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): NamedType = {
1984       def reload(): NamedType = {
1985         val allowPrivate = !lastSymbol.exists || lastSymbol.is(Private) && prefix.classSymbol == this.prefix.classSymbol
1986         var d = memberDenot(prefix, name, allowPrivate)
1987         if (d.isOverloaded && lastSymbol.exists)
1988           d = disambiguate(d,
1989                 if (lastSymbol.signature == Signature.NotAMethod) Signature.NotAMethod
1990                 else lastSymbol.asSeenFrom(prefix).signature)
1991         NamedType(prefix, name, d)
1992       }
1993       if (prefix eq this.prefix) this
1994       else if (lastDenotation == null) NamedType(prefix, designator)
1995       else designator match {
1996         case sym: Symbol =>
1997           if (infoDependsOnPrefix(sym, prefix) && !prefix.isArgPrefixOf(sym)) {
1998             val candidate = reload()
1999             val falseOverride = sym.isClass && candidate.symbol.exists && candidate.symbol != symbol
2000               // A false override happens if we rebind an inner class to another type with the same name
2001               // in an outer subclass. This is wrong, since classes do not override. We need to
2002               // return a type with the existing class info as seen from the new prefix instead.
2003             if (falseOverride) NamedType(prefix, sym.name, denot.asSeenFrom(prefix))
2004             else candidate
2005           }
2006           else NamedType(prefix, sym)
2007         case name: Name => reload()
2008       }
2009     }
2010 
2011     override def equals(that: Any) = that match {
2012       case that: NamedType =>
2013         this.designator == that.designator &&
2014         this.prefix == that.prefix
2015       case _ =>
2016         false
2017     }
2018 
2019     override def computeHash = unsupported("computeHash")
2020 
2021     override def eql(that: Type) = this eq that // safe because named types are hash-consed separately
2022   }

2024   /** A reference to an implicit definition. This can be either a TermRef or a
2025    *  Implicits.RenamedImplicitRef.
2026    */
2027   trait ImplicitRef {
2028     def implicitName(implicit ctx: Context): TermName
2029     def underlyingRef: TermRef
2030   }

2032   abstract case class TermRef(override val prefix: Type,
2033                               private var myDesignator: Designator)
2034     extends NamedType with SingletonType with ImplicitRef {
2035 
2036     type ThisType = TermRef
2037     type ThisName = TermName
2038 
2039     override def designator = myDesignator
2040     override protected def designator_=(d: Designator) = myDesignator = d
2041 
2042     //assert(name.toString != "<local Coder>")
2043     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
2044       val d = denot
2045       if (d.isOverloaded) NoType else d.info
2046     }
2047 
2048     override def isOverloaded(implicit ctx: Context) = denot.isOverloaded
2049 
2050     def alternatives(implicit ctx: Context): List[TermRef] =
2051       denot.alternatives.map(withDenot(_))
2052 
2053     def altsWith(p: Symbol => Boolean)(implicit ctx: Context): List[TermRef] =
2054       denot.altsWith(p).map(withDenot(_))
2055 
2056     def implicitName(implicit ctx: Context): TermName = name
2057     def underlyingRef = this
2058   }

2068     override protected def designator_=(d: Designator) = myDesignator = d

2071   }

2083   /** Assert current phase does not have erasure semantics */

2085     if (Config.checkUnerased) assert(!ctx.phase.erasedTypes)

2087   object NamedType {
2088     def isType(desig: Designator)(implicit ctx: Context) = desig match {
2089       case sym: Symbol => sym.isType
2090       case name: Name => name.isTypeName
2091     }
2092     def apply(prefix: Type, designator: Designator)(implicit ctx: Context) =
2093       if (isType(designator)) TypeRef.apply(prefix, designator)
2094       else TermRef.apply(prefix, designator)
2095     def apply(prefix: Type, designator: Name, denot: Denotation)(implicit ctx: Context) =
2096       if (designator.isTermName) TermRef.apply(prefix, designator.asTermName, denot)
2097       else TypeRef.apply(prefix, designator.asTypeName, denot)
2098   }

2100   object TermRef {
2101 
2102     /** Create a term ref with given designator */
2103     def apply(prefix: Type, desig: Designator)(implicit ctx: Context): TermRef =
2104       ctx.uniqueNamedTypes.enterIfNew(prefix, desig, isTerm = true).asInstanceOf[TermRef]
2105 
2106     /** Create a term ref with given initial denotation. The name of the reference is taken
2107      *  from the denotation's symbol if the latter exists, or else it is the given name.
2108      */
2109     def apply(prefix: Type, name: TermName, denot: Denotation)(implicit ctx: Context): TermRef =
2110       apply(prefix, if (denot.symbol.exists) denot.symbol.asTerm else name).withDenot(denot)
2111   }

2113   object TypeRef {

2115     /** Create a type ref with given prefix and name */
2116     def apply(prefix: Type, desig: Designator)(implicit ctx: Context): TypeRef =
2117       ctx.uniqueNamedTypes.enterIfNew(prefix, desig, isTerm = false).asInstanceOf[TypeRef]
2118 
2119     /** Create a type ref with given initial denotation. The name of the reference is taken
2120      *  from the denotation's symbol if the latter exists, or else it is the given name.
2121      */
2122     def apply(prefix: Type, name: TypeName, denot: Denotation)(implicit ctx: Context): TypeRef =
2123       apply(prefix, if (denot.symbol.exists) denot.symbol.asType else name).withDenot(denot)
2124   }

2128   /** The type cls.this
2129    *  @param tref    A type ref which indicates the class `cls`.
2130    *  Note: we do not pass a class symbol directly, because symbols
2131    *  do not survive runs whereas typerefs do.
2132    */
2133   abstract case class ThisType(tref: TypeRef) extends CachedProxyType with SingletonType {
2134     def cls(implicit ctx: Context): ClassSymbol = tref.stableInRunSymbol.asClass
2135     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2136       if (ctx.erasedTypes) tref
2137       else cls.info match {
2138         case cinfo: ClassInfo => cinfo.selfType
2139         case cinfo: ErrorType if ctx.mode.is(Mode.Interactive) => cinfo
2140           // can happen in IDE if `cls` is stale
2141       }
2142 
2143     override def computeHash = doHash(tref)
2144 
2145     override def eql(that: Type) = that match {
2146       case that: ThisType => tref.eq(that.tref)
2147       case _ => false
2148     }
2149   }
2150 
2151   final class CachedThisType(tref: TypeRef) extends ThisType(tref)
2152 
2153   object ThisType {
2154     /** Normally one should use ClassSymbol#thisType instead */
2155     def raw(tref: TypeRef)(implicit ctx: Context) =
2156       unique(new CachedThisType(tref))
2157   }

2159   /** The type of a super reference cls.super where
2160    *  `thistpe` is cls.this and `supertpe` is the type of the value referenced
2161    *  by `super`.
2162    */
2163   abstract case class SuperType(thistpe: Type, supertpe: Type) extends CachedProxyType with SingletonType {
2164     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context) = supertpe
2165     override def superType(implicit ctx: Context) =
2166       thistpe.baseType(supertpe.typeSymbol)
2167     def derivedSuperType(thistpe: Type, supertpe: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) =
2168       if ((thistpe eq this.thistpe) && (supertpe eq this.supertpe)) this
2169       else SuperType(thistpe, supertpe)
2170 
2171     override def computeHash = doHash(thistpe, supertpe)
2172 
2173     override def eql(that: Type) = that match {
2174       case that: SuperType => thistpe.eq(that.thistpe) && supertpe.eq(that.supertpe)
2175       case _ => false
2176     }
2177   }
2178 
2179   final class CachedSuperType(thistpe: Type, supertpe: Type) extends SuperType(thistpe, supertpe)
2180 
2181   object SuperType {

2183       assert(thistpe != NoPrefix)
2184       unique(new CachedSuperType(thistpe, supertpe))
2185     }

2204   case class LazyRef(private var refFn: Context => Type) extends UncachedProxyType with ValueType {
2205     private[this] var myRef: Type = null
2206     private[this] var computed = false
2207     def ref(implicit ctx: Context) = {
2208       if (computed) assert(myRef != null)
2209       else {
2210         computed = true
2211         myRef = refFn(ctx)
2212         refFn = null
2213       }
2214       myRef
2215     }
2216     def evaluating = computed && myRef == null
2217     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context) = ref
2218     override def toString = s"LazyRef(${if (computed) myRef else "..."})"
2219     override def equals(other: Any) = this.eq(other.asInstanceOf[AnyRef])
2220     override def hashCode = System.identityHashCode(this)
2221   }

2225   abstract class RefinedOrRecType extends CachedProxyType with ValueType {
2226     def parent: Type
2227   }

2229   /** A refined type parent { refinement }
2230    *  @param refinedName  The name of the refinement declaration
2231    *  @param infoFn: A function that produces the info of the refinement declaration,
2232    *                 given the refined type itself.
2233    */
2234   abstract case class RefinedType(parent: Type, refinedName: Name, refinedInfo: Type) extends RefinedOrRecType {
2235 
2236     if (refinedName.isTermName) assert(refinedInfo.isInstanceOf[TermType])
2237     else assert(refinedInfo.isInstanceOf[TypeType], this)
2238     assert(!refinedName.is(NameKinds.ExpandedName), this)
2239 
2240     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context) = parent
2241 
2242     private def badInst =
2243       throw new AssertionError(s"bad instantiation: $this")
2244 
2245     def checkInst(implicit ctx: Context): this.type = this // debug hook
2246 
2247     def derivedRefinedType(parent: Type, refinedName: Name, refinedInfo: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2248       if ((parent eq this.parent) && (refinedName eq this.refinedName) && (refinedInfo eq this.refinedInfo)) this
2249       else RefinedType(parent, refinedName, refinedInfo)
2250 
2251     /** Add this refinement to `parent`, provided `refinedName` is a member of `parent`. */
2252     def wrapIfMember(parent: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2253       if (parent.member(refinedName).exists) derivedRefinedType(parent, refinedName, refinedInfo)
2254       else parent
2255 
2256     override def computeHash = doHash(refinedName, refinedInfo, parent)
2257 
2258     override def eql(that: Type) = that match {
2259       case that: RefinedType =>
2260         refinedName.eq(that.refinedName) &&
2261         refinedInfo.eq(that.refinedInfo) &&
2262         parent.eq(that.parent)
2263       case _ => false
2264     }
2265   }

2267   class CachedRefinedType(parent: Type, refinedName: Name, refinedInfo: Type)
2268   extends RefinedType(parent, refinedName, refinedInfo)
2269 
2270   object RefinedType {
2271     @tailrec def make(parent: Type, names: List[Name], infos: List[Type])(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2272       if (names.isEmpty) parent
2273       else make(RefinedType(parent, names.head, infos.head), names.tail, infos.tail)
2274 
2275     def apply(parent: Type, name: Name, info: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): RefinedType = {
2276       assert(!ctx.erasedTypes)
2277       unique(new CachedRefinedType(parent, name, info)).checkInst
2278     }
2279   }

2281   class RecType(parentExp: RecType => Type) extends RefinedOrRecType with BindingType {
2282 
2283     // See discussion in findMember#goRec why these vars are needed
2284     private[Types] var opened: Boolean = false
2285     private[Types] var openedTwice: Boolean = false
2286 
2287     val parent = parentExp(this)
2288 
2289     private[this] var myRecThis: RecThis = null
2290 
2291     def recThis: RecThis = {
2292       if (myRecThis == null) myRecThis = new RecThis(this) {}
2293       myRecThis
2294     }
2295 
2296     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context): Type = parent
2297 
2298     def derivedRecType(parent: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): RecType =
2299       if (parent eq this.parent) this
2300       else RecType(rt => parent.substRecThis(this, rt.recThis))
2301 
2302     def rebind(parent: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2303       if (parent eq this.parent) this
2304       else RecType.closeOver(rt => parent.substRecThis(this, rt.recThis))
2305 
2306     def isReferredToBy(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = {
2307       val refacc = new TypeAccumulator[Boolean] {
2308         override def apply(x: Boolean, tp: Type) = x || {
2309           tp match {
2310             case tp: TypeRef => apply(x, tp.prefix)
2311             case tp: RecThis => RecType.this eq tp.binder
2312             case tp: LazyRef => true // To be safe, assume a reference exists
2313             case _ => foldOver(x, tp)
2314           }
2315         }
2316       }
2317       refacc.apply(false, tp)
2318     }
2319 
2320     override def computeHash = doHash(parent)
2321 
2322     override def equals(that: Any) = that match {
2323       case that: RecType => parent == that.parent
2324       case _ => false
2325     }
2326 
2327     override def eql(that: Type) = that match {
2328       case that: RecType => parent.eq(that.parent)
2329       case _ => false
2330     }
2331 
2332     override def toString = s"RecType($parent | $hashCode)"
2333 
2334     private def checkInst(implicit ctx: Context): this.type = this // debug hook
2335   }
2336 
2337   object RecType {
2338 
2339     /** Create a RecType, normalizing its contents. This means:
2340      *
2341      *   1. Nested Rec types on the type's spine are merged with the outer one.
2342      *   2. Any refinement of the form `type T = z.T` on the spine of the type
2343      *      where `z` refers to the created rec-type is replaced by
2344      *      `type T`. This avoids infinite recursons later when we
2345      *      try to follow these references.
2346      *   TODO: Figure out how to guarantee absence of cycles
2347      *         of length > 1
2348      */
2349     def apply(parentExp: RecType => Type)(implicit ctx: Context): RecType = {
2350       val rt = new RecType(parentExp)
2351       def normalize(tp: Type): Type = tp.stripTypeVar match {
2352         case tp: RecType =>
2353           normalize(tp.parent.substRecThis(tp, rt.recThis))
2354         case tp @ RefinedType(parent, rname, rinfo) =>
2355           val rinfo1 = rinfo match {
2356             case TypeAlias(ref @ TypeRef(RecThis(`rt`), _)) if ref.name == rname => TypeBounds.empty
2357             case _ => rinfo
2358           }
2359           tp.derivedRefinedType(normalize(parent), rname, rinfo1)
2360         case tp =>
2361           tp
2362       }
2363       unique(rt.derivedRecType(normalize(rt.parent))).checkInst
2364     }
2365     def closeOver(parentExp: RecType => Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = {
2366       val rt = this(parentExp)
2367       if (rt.isReferredToBy(rt.parent)) rt else rt.parent
2368     }
2369   }
2370 
2371   // --- AndType/OrType ---------------------------------------------------------------
2372 
2373   trait AndOrType extends ValueType { // todo: check where we can simplify using AndOrType
2374     def tp1: Type
2375     def tp2: Type
2376     def isAnd: Boolean
2377     def derivedAndOrType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type  // needed?
2378 
2379     private[this] var myBaseClassesPeriod: Period = Nowhere
2380     private[this] var myBaseClasses: List[ClassSymbol] = _
2381 
2382     /** Base classes of And are the merge of the operand base classes
2383      *  For OrTypes, it's the intersection.
2384      */
2385     override final def baseClasses(implicit ctx: Context) = {
2386       if (myBaseClassesPeriod != ctx.period) {
2387         val bcs1 = tp1.baseClasses
2388         val bcs1set = BaseClassSet(bcs1)
2389         def recur(bcs2: List[ClassSymbol]): List[ClassSymbol] = bcs2 match {
2390           case bc2 :: bcs2rest =>
2391             if (isAnd)
2392               if (bcs1set contains bc2)
2393                 if (bc2.is(Trait)) recur(bcs2rest)
2394                 else bcs1 // common class, therefore rest is the same in both sequences
2395               else bc2 :: recur(bcs2rest)
2396             else
2397               if (bcs1set contains bc2)
2398                 if (bc2.is(Trait)) bc2 :: recur(bcs2rest)
2399                 else bcs2
2400               else recur(bcs2rest)
2401           case nil =>
2402             if (isAnd) bcs1 else bcs2
2403         }
2404         myBaseClasses = recur(tp2.baseClasses)
2405         myBaseClassesPeriod = ctx.period
2406       }
2407       myBaseClasses
2408     }
2409   }
2410 
2411   abstract case class AndType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type) extends CachedGroundType with AndOrType {
2412 
2413     def isAnd = true
2414 
2415     def derivedAndType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2416       if ((tp1 eq this.tp1) && (tp2 eq this.tp2)) this
2417       else AndType.make(tp1, tp2, checkValid = true)
2418 
2419     def derived_& (tp1: Type, tp2: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2420       if ((tp1 eq this.tp1) && (tp2 eq this.tp2)) this
2421       else tp1 & tp2
2422 
2423     def derivedAndOrType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2424       derivedAndType(tp1, tp2)
2425 
2426     override def computeHash = doHash(tp1, tp2)
2427 
2428     override def eql(that: Type) = that match {
2429       case that: AndType => tp1.eq(that.tp1) && tp2.eq(that.tp2)
2430       case _ => false
2431     }
2432   }
2433 
2434   final class CachedAndType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type) extends AndType(tp1, tp2)
2435 
2436   object AndType {
2437     def apply(tp1: Type, tp2: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): AndType = {
2438       assert(tp1.isInstanceOf[ValueTypeOrWildcard] &&
2439              tp2.isInstanceOf[ValueTypeOrWildcard], i"$tp1 & $tp2 / " + s"$tp1 & $tp2")
2440       unchecked(tp1, tp2)
2441     }
2442 
2443     def unchecked(tp1: Type, tp2: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): AndType = {
2444       assertUnerased()
2445       unique(new CachedAndType(tp1, tp2))
2446     }
2447 
2448     /** Make an AndType using `op` unless clearly unnecessary (i.e. without
2449      *  going through `&`).
2450      */
2451     def make(tp1: Type, tp2: Type, checkValid: Boolean = false)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2452       if ((tp1 eq tp2) || (tp2 eq defn.AnyType))
2453         tp1
2454       else if (tp1 eq defn.AnyType)
2455         tp2
2456       else
2457         if (checkValid) apply(tp1, tp2) else unchecked(tp1, tp2)
2458   }

2460   abstract case class OrType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type) extends CachedGroundType with AndOrType {
2461 
2462     assert(tp1.isInstanceOf[ValueTypeOrWildcard] &&
2463            tp2.isInstanceOf[ValueTypeOrWildcard], s"$tp1 $tp2")
2464     def isAnd = false
2465 
2466     private[this] var myJoin: Type = _
2467     private[this] var myJoinPeriod: Period = Nowhere
2468 
2469     /** Replace or type by the closest non-or type above it */
2470     def join(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
2471       if (myJoinPeriod != ctx.period) {
2472         myJoin = ctx.orDominator(this)
2473         core.println(i"join of $this == $myJoin")
2474         assert(myJoin != this)
2475         myJoinPeriod = ctx.period
2476       }
2477       myJoin
2478     }
2479 
2480     def derivedOrType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2481       if ((tp1 eq this.tp1) && (tp2 eq this.tp2)) this
2482       else OrType.make(tp1, tp2)
2483 
2484     def derivedAndOrType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2485       derivedOrType(tp1, tp2)
2486 
2487     override def computeHash = doHash(tp1, tp2)
2488 
2489     override def eql(that: Type) = that match {
2490       case that: OrType => tp1.eq(that.tp1) && tp2.eq(that.tp2)
2491       case _ => false
2492     }
2493   }
2494 
2495   final class CachedOrType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type) extends OrType(tp1, tp2)
2496 
2497   object OrType {
2498     def apply(tp1: Type, tp2: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = {
2499       assertUnerased()
2500       unique(new CachedOrType(tp1, tp2))
2501     }
2502     def make(tp1: Type, tp2: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2503       if (tp1 eq tp2) tp1
2504       else apply(tp1, tp2)
2505   }

2509   // Note: method types are cached whereas poly types are not. The reason
2510   // is that most poly types are cyclic via poly params,
2511   // and therefore two different poly types would never be equal.
2512 
2513   /** A trait that mixes in functionality for signature caching */
2514   trait MethodicType extends TermType {
2515 
2516     private[this] var mySignature: Signature = _
2517     private[this] var mySignatureRunId: Int = NoRunId
2518 
2519     protected def computeSignature(implicit ctx: Context): Signature
2520 
2521     protected def resultSignature(implicit ctx: Context) = try resultType match {
2522       case rtp: MethodicType => rtp.signature
2523       case tp =>
2524         if (tp.isRef(defn.UnitClass)) Signature(Nil, defn.UnitClass.fullName.asTypeName)
2525         else Signature(tp, isJava = false)
2526     }
2527     catch {
2528       case ex: AssertionError =>
2529         println(i"failure while taking result signature of $this: $resultType")
2530         throw ex
2531     }
2532 
2533     final override def signature(implicit ctx: Context): Signature = {
2534       if (ctx.runId != mySignatureRunId) {
2535         mySignature = computeSignature
2536         if (!mySignature.isUnderDefined) mySignatureRunId = ctx.runId
2537       }
2538       mySignature
2539     }
2540   }

2542   /** A by-name parameter type of the form `=> T`, or the type of a method with no parameter list. */
2543   abstract case class ExprType(resType: Type)
2544   extends CachedProxyType with TermType with MethodicType {
2545     override def resultType(implicit ctx: Context): Type = resType
2546     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context): Type = resType
2547 
2548     def computeSignature(implicit ctx: Context): Signature = resultSignature
2549 
2550     def derivedExprType(resType: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) =
2551       if (resType eq this.resType) this else ExprType(resType)
2552 
2553     override def computeHash = doHash(resType)
2554 
2555     override def eql(that: Type) = that match {
2556       case that: ExprType => resType.eq(that.resType)
2557       case _ => false
2558     }
2559   }
