2570   /** The lambda type square:
2571    *
2572    *    LambdaType   |   TermLambda      |   TypeLambda
2573    *    -------------+-------------------+------------------
2574    *    HKLambda     |   HKTermLambda    |   HKTypeLambda
2575    *    MethodOrPoly |   MethodType	     |   PolyType
2576    */
2577   trait LambdaType extends BindingType with TermType { self =>
2578     type ThisName <: Name
2579     type PInfo <: Type
2580     type This <: LambdaType{type PInfo = self.PInfo}
2581     type ParamRefType <: ParamRef
2582 
2583     def paramNames: List[ThisName]
2584     def paramInfos: List[PInfo]
2585     def resType: Type
2586     protected def newParamRef(n: Int): ParamRefType
2587 
2588     override def resultType(implicit ctx: Context) = resType
2589 
2590     def isDependent(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean
2591     def isParamDependent(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean
2592 
2593     final def isTermLambda = isInstanceOf[TermLambda]
2594     final def isTypeLambda = isInstanceOf[TypeLambda]
2595     final def isHigherKinded = isInstanceOf[TypeProxy]
2596 
2597     private[this] var myParamRefs: List[ParamRefType] = null
2598 
2599     def paramRefs: List[ParamRefType] = {
2600       if (myParamRefs == null) myParamRefs = paramNames.indices.toList.map(newParamRef)
2601       myParamRefs
2602     }
2603 
2604     final def instantiate(argTypes: => List[Type])(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2605       if (isDependent) resultType.substParams(this, argTypes)
2606       else resultType
2607 
2608     def companion: LambdaTypeCompanion[ThisName, PInfo, This]
2609 
2610     /** The type `[tparams := paramRefs] tp`, where `tparams` can be
2611      *  either a list of type parameter symbols or a list of lambda parameters
2612      */
2613     def integrate(tparams: List[ParamInfo], tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2614       tparams match {
2615         case LambdaParam(lam, _) :: _ => tp.subst(lam, this)
2616         case params: List[Symbol @unchecked] => tp.subst(params, paramRefs)
2617       }
2618 
2619     final def derivedLambdaType(paramNames: List[ThisName] = this.paramNames,
2620                           paramInfos: List[PInfo] = this.paramInfos,
2621                           resType: Type = this.resType)(implicit ctx: Context) =
2622       if ((paramNames eq this.paramNames) && (paramInfos eq this.paramInfos) && (resType eq this.resType)) this
2623       else newLikeThis(paramNames, paramInfos, resType)
2624 
2625     final def newLikeThis(paramNames: List[ThisName], paramInfos: List[PInfo], resType: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): This =
2626       companion(paramNames)(
2627           x => paramInfos.mapConserve(_.subst(this, x).asInstanceOf[PInfo]),
2628           x => resType.subst(this, x))
2629 
2630     protected def prefixString: String
2631     final override def toString = s"$prefixString($paramNames, $paramInfos, $resType)"
2632   }
2633 
2634   abstract class HKLambda extends CachedProxyType with LambdaType {
2635     final override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context) = resType
2636 
2637     final override def computeHash = doHash(paramNames, resType, paramInfos)
2638 
2639     final override def equals(that: Any) = that match {
2640       case that: HKLambda =>
2641         paramNames == that.paramNames &&
2642         paramInfos == that.paramInfos &&
2643         resType == that.resType &&
2644         companion.eq(that.companion)
2645       case _ =>
2646         false
2647     }
2648 
2649     final override def eql(that: Type) = that match {
2650       case that: HKLambda =>
2651         paramNames.equals(that.paramNames) &&
2652         paramInfos.equals(that.paramInfos) &&
2653         resType.equals(that.resType) &&
2654         companion.eq(that.companion)
2655       case _ =>
2656         false
2657     }
2658   }

2660   trait MethodOrPoly extends LambdaType with MethodicType
2661 
2662   trait TermLambda extends LambdaType { thisLambdaType =>
2663     import DepStatus._
2664     type ThisName = TermName
2665     type PInfo = Type
2666     type This <: TermLambda
2667     type ParamRefType = TermParamRef
2668 
2669     override def resultType(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2670       if (dependencyStatus == FalseDeps) { // dealias all false dependencies
2671         val dealiasMap = new TypeMap {
2672           def apply(tp: Type) = tp match {
2673             case tp @ TypeRef(pre, _) =>
2674               tp.info match {
2675                 case TypeAlias(alias) if depStatus(NoDeps, pre) == TrueDeps => apply(alias)
2676                 case _ => mapOver(tp)
2677               }
2678             case _ =>
2679               mapOver(tp)
2680           }
2681         }
2682         dealiasMap(resType)
2683       }
2684       else resType
2685 
2686     private[this] var myDependencyStatus: DependencyStatus = Unknown
2687     private[this] var myParamDependencyStatus: DependencyStatus = Unknown
2688 
2689     private def depStatus(initial: DependencyStatus, tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): DependencyStatus = {
2690       def combine(x: DependencyStatus, y: DependencyStatus) = {
2691         val status = (x & StatusMask) max (y & StatusMask)
2692         val provisional = (x | y) & Provisional
2693         (if (status == TrueDeps) status else status | provisional).toByte
2694       }
2695       val depStatusAcc = new TypeAccumulator[DependencyStatus] {
2696         def apply(status: DependencyStatus, tp: Type) =
2697           if (status == TrueDeps) status
2698           else
2699             tp match {
2700               case TermParamRef(`thisLambdaType`, _) => TrueDeps
2701               case tp: TypeRef =>
2702                 val status1 = foldOver(status, tp)
2703                 tp.info match { // follow type alias to avoid dependency
2704                   case TypeAlias(alias) if status1 == TrueDeps && status != TrueDeps =>
2705                     combine(apply(status, alias), FalseDeps)
2706                   case _ =>
2707                     status1
2708                 }
2709               case tp: TypeVar if !tp.isInstantiated => combine(status, Provisional)
2710               case _ => foldOver(status, tp)
2711             }
2712       }
2713       depStatusAcc(initial, tp)
2714     }
2715 
2716     /** The dependency status of this method. Some examples:
2717      *
2718      *    class C extends { type S; type T = String }
2719      *    def f(x: C)(y: Boolean)   // dependencyStatus = NoDeps
2720      *    def f(x: C)(y: x.S)       // dependencyStatus = TrueDeps
2721      *    def f(x: C)(y: x.T)       // dependencyStatus = FalseDeps, i.e.
2722      *                              // dependency can be eliminated by dealiasing.
2723      */
2724     private def dependencyStatus(implicit ctx: Context): DependencyStatus = {
2725       if (myDependencyStatus != Unknown) myDependencyStatus
2726       else {
2727         val result = depStatus(NoDeps, resType)
2728         if ((result & Provisional) == 0) myDependencyStatus = result
2729         (result & StatusMask).toByte
2730       }
2731     }
2732 
2733     /** The parameter dependency status of this method. Analogous to `dependencyStatus`,
2734      *  but tracking dependencies in same parameter list.
2735      */
2736     private def paramDependencyStatus(implicit ctx: Context): DependencyStatus = {
2737       if (myParamDependencyStatus != Unknown) myParamDependencyStatus
2738       else {
2739         val result =
2740           if (paramInfos.isEmpty) NoDeps
2741           else (NoDeps /: paramInfos.tail)(depStatus(_, _))
2742         if ((result & Provisional) == 0) myParamDependencyStatus = result
2743         (result & StatusMask).toByte
2744       }
2745     }
2746 
2747     /** Does result type contain references to parameters of this method type,
2748      *  which cannot be eliminated by de-aliasing?
2749      */
2750     def isDependent(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = dependencyStatus == TrueDeps
2751 
2752     /** Does one of the parameter types contain references to earlier parameters
2753      *  of this method type which cannot be eliminated by de-aliasing?
2754      */
2755     def isParamDependent(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = paramDependencyStatus == TrueDeps
2756 
2757     def newParamRef(n: Int) = new TermParamRef(this, n) {}
2758 
2759     /** The least supertype of `resultType` that does not contain parameter dependencies */
2760     def nonDependentResultApprox(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2761       if (isDependent) {
2762         val dropDependencies = new ApproximatingTypeMap {
2763           def apply(tp: Type) = tp match {
2764             case tp @ TermParamRef(thisLambdaType, _) =>
2765               range(tp.bottomType, atVariance(1)(apply(tp.underlying)))
2766             case _ => mapOver(tp)
2767           }
2768         }
2769         dropDependencies(resultType)
2770       }
2771       else resultType
2772   }
2773 
2774   abstract case class MethodType(paramNames: List[TermName])(
2775       paramInfosExp: MethodType => List[Type],
2776       resultTypeExp: MethodType => Type)
2777     extends CachedGroundType with MethodOrPoly with TermLambda with NarrowCached { thisMethodType =>

2788     val resType = resultTypeExp(this)

2790

2792       resultSignature.prepend(paramInfos, isJavaMethod)
2793

2809         paramInfos.eqElements(that.paramInfos) &&

2819   final class CachedMethodType(paramNames: List[TermName])(paramInfosExp: MethodType => List[Type], resultTypeExp: MethodType => Type, val companion: MethodTypeCompanion)
2820     extends MethodType(paramNames)(paramInfosExp, resultTypeExp)

2822   abstract class LambdaTypeCompanion[N <: Name, PInfo <: Type, LT <: LambdaType] {
2823     def syntheticParamName(n: Int): N
2824 
2825     @sharable private val memoizedNames = new mutable.HashMap[Int, List[N]]
2826     def syntheticParamNames(n: Int): List[N] = synchronized {
2827       memoizedNames.getOrElseUpdate(n, (0 until n).map(syntheticParamName).toList)
2828     }
2829 
2830     def apply(paramNames: List[N])(paramInfosExp: LT => List[PInfo], resultTypeExp: LT => Type)(implicit ctx: Context): LT
2831     def apply(paramNames: List[N], paramInfos: List[PInfo], resultType: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): LT =
2832       apply(paramNames)(_ => paramInfos, _ => resultType)
2833     def apply(paramInfos: List[PInfo])(resultTypeExp: LT => Type)(implicit ctx: Context): LT =
2834       apply(syntheticParamNames(paramInfos.length))(_ => paramInfos, resultTypeExp)
2835     def apply(paramInfos: List[PInfo], resultType: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): LT =
2836       apply(syntheticParamNames(paramInfos.length), paramInfos, resultType)
2837 
2838     protected def paramName(param: ParamInfo.Of[N])(implicit ctx: Context): N =
2839       param.paramName
2840 
2841     protected def toPInfo(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): PInfo
2842 
2843     def fromParams[PI <: ParamInfo.Of[N]](params: List[PI], resultType: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2844       if (params.isEmpty) resultType
2845       else apply(params.map(paramName))(
2846         tl => params.map(param => toPInfo(tl.integrate(params, param.paramInfo))),
2847         tl => tl.integrate(params, resultType))
2848   }

2854   }

2856   abstract class TypeLambdaCompanion[LT <: TypeLambda]
2857   extends LambdaTypeCompanion[TypeName, TypeBounds, LT] {
2858     def toPInfo(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): TypeBounds = (tp: @unchecked) match {
2859       case tp: TypeBounds => tp
2860       case tp: ErrorType => TypeAlias(tp)

2865   abstract class MethodTypeCompanion extends TermLambdaCompanion[MethodType] { self =>
2866 
2867     /** Produce method type from parameter symbols, with special mappings for repeated
2868      *  and inline parameters:
2869      *   - replace @repeated annotations on Seq or Array types by <repeated> types
2870      *   - add @inlineParam to inline call-by-value parameters
2871      */
2872     def fromSymbols(params: List[Symbol], resultType: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = {
2873       def translateInline(tp: Type): Type = tp match {
2874         case _: ExprType => tp
2875         case _ => AnnotatedType(tp, Annotation(defn.InlineParamAnnot))
2876       }
2877       def paramInfo(param: Symbol) = {
2878         val paramType = param.info.annotatedToRepeated
2879         if (param.is(Inline)) translateInline(paramType) else paramType
2880       }
2881 
2882       apply(params.map(_.name.asTermName))(
2883          tl => params.map(p => tl.integrate(params, paramInfo(p))),
2884          tl => tl.integrate(params, resultType))
2885     }
2886 
2887     final def apply(paramNames: List[TermName])(paramInfosExp: MethodType => List[Type], resultTypeExp: MethodType => Type)(implicit ctx: Context): MethodType =
2888       checkValid(unique(new CachedMethodType(paramNames)(paramInfosExp, resultTypeExp, self)))
2889 
2890     def checkValid(mt: MethodType)(implicit ctx: Context): mt.type = {
2891       if (Config.checkMethodTypes)
2892         for ((paramInfo, idx) <- mt.paramInfos.zipWithIndex)
2893           paramInfo.foreachPart {
2894             case TermParamRef(`mt`, j) => assert(j < idx, mt)
2895             case _ =>
2896           }
2897       mt
2898     }
2899   }
2900 
2901   object MethodType extends MethodTypeCompanion
2902   object JavaMethodType extends MethodTypeCompanion
2903   object ImplicitMethodType extends MethodTypeCompanion
2904 
2905   /** A ternary extractor for MethodType */
2906   object MethodTpe {
2907     def unapply(mt: MethodType)(implicit ctx: Context) =
2908       Some((mt.paramNames, mt.paramInfos, mt.resultType))
2909   }

2911   trait TypeLambda extends LambdaType {
2912     type ThisName = TypeName
2913     type PInfo = TypeBounds
2914     type This <: TypeLambda
2915     type ParamRefType = TypeParamRef
2916 
2917     def isDependent(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = true
2918     def isParamDependent(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = true
2919 
2920     def newParamRef(n: Int) = new TypeParamRef(this, n) {}
2921 
2922     lazy val typeParams: List[LambdaParam] =
2923       paramNames.indices.toList.map(new LambdaParam(this, _))
2924 
2925     /** Instantiate parameter bounds by substituting parameters with given arguments */
2926     final def instantiateBounds(argTypes: List[Type])(implicit ctx: Context): List[Type] =
2927       paramInfos.mapConserve(_.substParams(this, argTypes))
2928 
2929     def derivedLambdaAbstraction(paramNames: List[TypeName], paramInfos: List[TypeBounds], resType: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
2930       resType match {
2931         case resType @ TypeAlias(alias) =>
2932           resType.derivedTypeAlias(newLikeThis(paramNames, paramInfos, alias))
2933         case resType @ TypeBounds(lo, hi) =>
2934           resType.derivedTypeBounds(
2935             if (lo.isRef(defn.NothingClass)) lo else newLikeThis(paramNames, paramInfos, lo),
2936             newLikeThis(paramNames, paramInfos, hi))
2937         case _ =>
2938           derivedLambdaType(paramNames, paramInfos, resType)
2939       }
2940   }
2941 
2942   /** A type lambda of the form `[X_0 B_0, ..., X_n B_n] => T`
2943    *  Variances are encoded in parameter names. A name starting with `+`
2944    *  designates a covariant parameter, a name starting with `-` designates
2945    *  a contravariant parameter, and every other name designates a non-variant parameter.
2946    *
2947    *  @param  paramNames      The names `X_0`, ..., `X_n`
2948    *  @param  paramInfosExp  A function that, given the polytype itself, returns the
2949    *                          parameter bounds `B_1`, ..., `B_n`
2950    *  @param  resultTypeExp   A function that, given the polytype itself, returns the
2951    *                          result type `T`.
2952    */
2953   class HKTypeLambda(val paramNames: List[TypeName])(
2954       paramInfosExp: HKTypeLambda => List[TypeBounds], resultTypeExp: HKTypeLambda => Type)
2955   extends HKLambda with TypeLambda {
2956     type This = HKTypeLambda
2957     def companion = HKTypeLambda
2958 
2959     val paramInfos: List[TypeBounds] = paramInfosExp(this)
2960     val resType: Type = resultTypeExp(this)
2961 
2962     assert(resType.isInstanceOf[TermType], this)
2963     assert(paramNames.nonEmpty)
2964 
2965     protected def prefixString = "HKTypeLambda"
2966   }
2967 
2968   /** The type of a polymorphic method. It has the same form as HKTypeLambda,
2969    *  except it applies to terms and parameters do not have variances.
2970    */
2971   class PolyType(val paramNames: List[TypeName])(
2972       paramInfosExp: PolyType => List[TypeBounds], resultTypeExp: PolyType => Type)
2973   extends UncachedGroundType with MethodOrPoly with TypeLambda {
2974 
2975     type This = PolyType
2976     def companion = PolyType
2977 
2978     val paramInfos: List[TypeBounds] = paramInfosExp(this)
2979     val resType: Type = resultTypeExp(this)
2980 
2981     assert(resType.isInstanceOf[TermType], this)
2982     assert(paramNames.nonEmpty)
2983 
2984     def computeSignature(implicit ctx: Context) = resultSignature
2985 
2986     /** Merge nested polytypes into one polytype. nested polytypes are normally not supported
2987      *  but can arise as temporary data structures.
2988      */
2989     def flatten(implicit ctx: Context): PolyType = resType match {
2990       case that: PolyType =>
2991         val shiftedSubst = (x: PolyType) => new TypeMap {
2992           def apply(t: Type) = t match {
2993             case TypeParamRef(`that`, n) => x.paramRefs(n + paramNames.length)
2994             case t => mapOver(t)
2995           }
2996         }
2997         PolyType(paramNames ++ that.paramNames)(
2998           x => this.paramInfos.mapConserve(_.subst(this, x).bounds) ++
2999                that.paramInfos.mapConserve(shiftedSubst(x)(_).bounds),
3000           x => shiftedSubst(x)(that.resultType).subst(this, x))
3001       case _ => this
3002     }
3003 
3004     protected def prefixString = "PolyType"
3005   }
3006 
3007   object HKTypeLambda extends TypeLambdaCompanion[HKTypeLambda] {
3008     def apply(paramNames: List[TypeName])(
3009         paramInfosExp: HKTypeLambda => List[TypeBounds],
3010         resultTypeExp: HKTypeLambda => Type)(implicit ctx: Context): HKTypeLambda = {
3011       unique(new HKTypeLambda(paramNames)(paramInfosExp, resultTypeExp))
3012     }
3013 
3014     def unapply(tl: HKTypeLambda): Some[(List[LambdaParam], Type)] =
3015       Some((tl.typeParams, tl.resType))
3016 
3017     def any(n: Int)(implicit ctx: Context) =
3018       apply(syntheticParamNames(n))(
3019         pt => List.fill(n)(TypeBounds.empty), pt => defn.AnyType)
3020 
3021     override def paramName(param: ParamInfo.Of[TypeName])(implicit ctx: Context): TypeName =
3022       param.paramName.withVariance(param.paramVariance)
3023 
3024     /** Distributes Lambda inside type bounds. Examples:
3025   	 *
3026    	 *      type T[X] = U        becomes    type T = [X] -> U
3027    	 *      type T[X] <: U       becomes    type T >: Nothign <: ([X] -> U)
3028      *      type T[X] >: L <: U  becomes    type T >: ([X] -> L) <: ([X] -> U)
3029      */
3030     override def fromParams[PI <: ParamInfo.Of[TypeName]](params: List[PI], resultType: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
3031       def expand(tp: Type) = super.fromParams(params, tp)
3032       resultType match {
3033         case rt: TypeAlias =>
3034           rt.derivedTypeAlias(expand(rt.alias))
3035         case rt @ TypeBounds(lo, hi) =>
3036           rt.derivedTypeBounds(
3037             if (lo.isRef(defn.NothingClass)) lo else expand(lo), expand(hi))
3038         case rt =>
3039           expand(rt)
3040       }
3041     }
3042   }
3043 
3044   object PolyType extends TypeLambdaCompanion[PolyType] {
3045     def apply(paramNames: List[TypeName])(
3046         paramInfosExp: PolyType => List[TypeBounds],
3047         resultTypeExp: PolyType => Type)(implicit ctx: Context): PolyType = {
3048       unique(new PolyType(paramNames)(paramInfosExp, resultTypeExp))
3049     }
3050 
3051     def unapply(tl: PolyType): Some[(List[LambdaParam], Type)] =
3052       Some((tl.typeParams, tl.resType))
3053 
3054     def any(n: Int)(implicit ctx: Context) =
3055       apply(syntheticParamNames(n))(
3056         pt => List.fill(n)(TypeBounds.empty), pt => defn.AnyType)
3057   }

3059   private object DepStatus {
3060     type DependencyStatus = Byte
3061     final val Unknown: DependencyStatus = 0   // not yet computed
3062     final val NoDeps: DependencyStatus = 1    // no dependent parameters found
3063     final val FalseDeps: DependencyStatus = 2 // all dependent parameters are prefixes of non-depended alias types
3064     final val TrueDeps: DependencyStatus = 3  // some truly dependent parameters exist
3065     final val StatusMask: DependencyStatus = 3 // the bits indicating actual dependency status
3066     final val Provisional: DependencyStatus = 4  // set if dependency status can still change due to type variable instantiations
3067   }

3071   /** The parameter of a type lambda */
3072   case class LambdaParam(tl: TypeLambda, n: Int) extends ParamInfo {
3073     type ThisName = TypeName
3074     def isTypeParam(implicit ctx: Context) = tl.paramNames.head.isTypeName
3075     def paramName(implicit ctx: Context) = tl.paramNames(n)
3076     def paramInfo(implicit ctx: Context) = tl.paramInfos(n)
3077     def paramInfoAsSeenFrom(pre: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = paramInfo.asSeenFrom(pre, pre.classSymbol)
3078     def paramInfoOrCompleter(implicit ctx: Context): Type = paramInfo
3079     def paramVariance(implicit ctx: Context): Int = tl.paramNames(n).variance
3080     def paramRef(implicit ctx: Context): Type = tl.paramRefs(n)
3081   }
3082 
3083   /** A type application `C[T_1, ..., T_n]` */
3084   abstract case class AppliedType(tycon: Type, args: List[Type])
3085   extends CachedProxyType with ValueType {
3086 
3087     private[this] var validSuper: Period = Nowhere
3088     private[this] var cachedSuper: Type = _
3089 
3090     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context): Type = tycon
3091 
3092     override def superType(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
3093       if (ctx.period != validSuper) {
3094         validSuper = ctx.period
3095         cachedSuper = tycon match {
3096           case tycon: HKTypeLambda => defn.AnyType
3097           case tycon: TypeVar if !tycon.inst.exists =>
3098             // supertype not stable, since underlying might change
3099             validSuper = Nowhere
3100             tycon.underlying.applyIfParameterized(args)
3101           case tycon: TypeRef if tycon.symbol.isClass =>
3102             tycon
3103           case tycon: TypeProxy =>
3104             if (tycon.typeSymbol.is(Provisional)) validSuper = Nowhere
3105             tycon.superType.applyIfParameterized(args)
3106           case _ => defn.AnyType
3107         }
3108       }
3109       cachedSuper
3110     }
3111 
3112     def lowerBound(implicit ctx: Context) = tycon.stripTypeVar match {
3113       case tycon: TypeRef =>
3114         tycon.info match {
3115           case TypeBounds(lo, hi) =>
3116             if (lo eq hi) superType // optimization, can profit from caching in this case
3117             else lo.applyIfParameterized(args)
3118           case _ => NoType
3119         }
3120       case _ =>
3121         NoType
3122     }
3123 
3124     def typeParams(implicit ctx: Context): List[ParamInfo] = {
3125       val tparams = tycon.typeParams
3126       if (tparams.isEmpty) HKTypeLambda.any(args.length).typeParams else tparams
3127     }
3128 
3129     def derivedAppliedType(tycon: Type, args: List[Type])(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
3130       if ((tycon eq this.tycon) && (args eq this.args)) this
3131       else tycon.appliedTo(args)
3132   }
3133 
3134   final class CachedAppliedType(tycon: Type, args: List[Type], hc: Int) extends AppliedType(tycon, args) {
3135     myHash = hc
3136     override def computeHash = unsupported("computeHash")
3137     override def eql(that: Type) = this eq that // safe because applied types are hash-consed separately
3138   }
3139 
3140   object AppliedType {
3141     def apply(tycon: Type, args: List[Type])(implicit ctx: Context) = {
3142       assertUnerased()
3143       ctx.base.uniqueAppliedTypes.enterIfNew(tycon, args)
3144     }
3145   }

3147   // ----- BoundTypes: ParamRef, RecThis ----------------------------------------
3148 
3149   abstract class BoundType extends CachedProxyType with ValueType {
3150     type BT <: Type
3151     val binder: BT
3152     def copyBoundType(bt: BT): Type
3153   }
3154 
3155   abstract class ParamRef extends BoundType {
3156     type BT <: LambdaType
3157     def paramNum: Int
3158     def paramName: binder.ThisName = binder.paramNames(paramNum)
3159 
3160     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
3161       val infos = binder.paramInfos
3162       if (infos == null) NoType // this can happen if the referenced generic type is not initialized yet
3163       else infos(paramNum)
3164     }
3165 
3166     override def computeHash = doHash(paramNum, binder.identityHash)
3167 
3168     override def equals(that: Any) = that match {
3169       case that: ParamRef => binder.eq(that.binder) && paramNum == that.paramNum
3170       case _ => false
3171     }
3172 
3173     protected def kindString: String
3174 
3175     override def toString =
3176       try s"${kindString}ParamRef($paramName)"
3177       catch {
3178         case ex: IndexOutOfBoundsException => s"ParamRef(<bad index: $paramNum>)"
3179       }
3180   }
3181 
3182   /** Only created in `binder.paramRefs`. Use `binder.paramRefs(paramNum)` to
3183    *  refer to `TermParamRef(binder, paramNum)`.
3184    */
3185   abstract case class TermParamRef(binder: TermLambda, paramNum: Int) extends ParamRef with SingletonType {
3186     type BT = TermLambda
3187     def kindString = "Term"
3188     def copyBoundType(bt: BT) = bt.paramRefs(paramNum)
3189   }
3190 
3191   /** Only created in `binder.paramRefs`. Use `binder.paramRefs(paramNum)` to
3192    *  refer to `TypeParamRef(binder, paramNum)`.
3193    */
3194   abstract case class TypeParamRef(binder: TypeLambda, paramNum: Int) extends ParamRef {
3195     type BT = TypeLambda
3196     def kindString = "Type"
3197     def copyBoundType(bt: BT) = bt.paramRefs(paramNum)
3198 
3199     /** Looking only at the structure of `bound`, is one of the following true?
3200      *     - fromBelow and param <:< bound
3201      *     - !fromBelow and param >:> bound
3202      */
3203     def occursIn(bound: Type, fromBelow: Boolean)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = bound.stripTypeVar match {
3204       case bound: ParamRef => bound == this
3205       case bound: AndOrType =>
3206         def occ1 = occursIn(bound.tp1, fromBelow)
3207         def occ2 = occursIn(bound.tp2, fromBelow)
3208         if (fromBelow == bound.isAnd) occ1 && occ2 else occ1 || occ2
3209       case _ => false
3210     }
3211   }
3212 
3213   /** a self-reference to an enclosing recursive type. The only creation method is
3214    *  `binder.recThis`, returning `RecThis(binder)`.
3215    */
3216   abstract case class RecThis(binder: RecType) extends BoundType with SingletonType {
3217     type BT = RecType
3218     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context) = binder
3219     def copyBoundType(bt: BT) = bt.recThis
3220 
3221     // need to customize hashCode and equals to prevent infinite recursion
3222     // between RecTypes and RecRefs.
3223     override def computeHash = addDelta(binder.identityHash, 41)
3224 
3225     override def equals(that: Any) = that match {
3226       case that: RecThis => binder.eq(that.binder)
3227       case _ => false
3228     }
3229 
3230     override def toString =
3231       try s"RecThis(${binder.hashCode})"
3232       catch {
3233         case ex: NullPointerException => s"RecThis(<under construction>)"
3234       }
3235   }

3239   /** A skolem type reference with underlying type `binder`. */
3240   case class SkolemType(info: Type) extends UncachedProxyType with ValueType with SingletonType {
3241     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context) = info
3242     def derivedSkolemType(info: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) =
3243       if (info eq this.info) this else SkolemType(info)
3244     override def hashCode: Int = identityHash
3245     override def equals(that: Any) = this.eq(that.asInstanceOf[AnyRef])
3246 
3247     def withName(name: Name): this.type = { myRepr = name; this }
3248 
3249     private[this] var myRepr: Name = null
3250     def repr(implicit ctx: Context): Name = {
3251       if (myRepr == null) myRepr = SkolemName.fresh()
3252       myRepr
3253     }
3254 
3255     override def toString = s"Skolem($hashCode)"
3256   }

3258   // ------------ Type variables ----------------------------------------
3259 
3260   /** In a TypeApply tree, a TypeVar is created for each argument type to be inferred.
3261    *  Every type variable is referred to by exactly one inferred type parameter of some
3262    *  TypeApply tree.
3263    *
3264    *  A type variable is essentially a switch that models some part of a substitution.
3265    *  It is first linked to `origin`, a poly param that's in the current constraint set.
3266    *  It can then be (once) instantiated to some other type. The instantiation is
3267    *  recorded in the type variable itself, or else, if the current type state
3268    *  is different from the variable's creation state (meaning unrolls are possible)
3269    *  in the current typer state.
3270    *
3271    *  @param  origin        The parameter that's tracked by the type variable.
3272    *  @param  creatorState  The typer state in which the variable was created.
3273    *  @param  bindingTree   The TypeTree which introduces the type variable, or EmptyTree
3274    *                        if the type variable does not correspond to a source term.
3275    *  @paran  owner         The current owner if the context where the variable was created.
3276    *
3277    *  `owningTree` and `owner` are used to determine whether a type-variable can be instantiated
3278    *  at some given point. See `Inferencing#interpolateUndetVars`.
3279    */
3280   final class TypeVar(val origin: TypeParamRef, creatorState: TyperState, val bindingTree: untpd.Tree, val owner: Symbol) extends CachedProxyType with ValueType {
3281 
3282     /** The permanent instance type of the variable, or NoType is none is given yet */
3283     private[this] var myInst: Type = NoType
3284 
3285     private[core] def inst = myInst
3286     private[core] def inst_=(tp: Type) = {
3287       myInst = tp
3288       if (tp.exists) owningState = null // no longer needed; null out to avoid a memory leak
3289     }
3290 
3291     /** The state owning the variable. This is at first `creatorState`, but it can
3292      *  be changed to an enclosing state on a commit.
3293      */
3294     private[core] var owningState = new WeakReference(creatorState)
3295 
3296     /** The instance type of this variable, or NoType if the variable is currently
3297      *  uninstantiated
3298      */
3299     def instanceOpt(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
3300       if (inst.exists) inst else {
3301         ctx.typerState.ephemeral = true
3302         ctx.typerState.instType(this)
3303       }
3304 
3305     /** Is the variable already instantiated? */
3306     def isInstantiated(implicit ctx: Context) = instanceOpt.exists
3307 
3308     /** Instantiate variable with given type */
3309     def instantiateWith(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
3310       assert(tp ne this, s"self instantiation of ${tp.show}, constraint = ${ctx.typerState.constraint.show}")
3311       typr.println(s"instantiating ${this.show} with ${tp.show}")
3312       if ((ctx.typerState eq owningState.get) && !ctx.typeComparer.subtypeCheckInProgress)
3313         inst = tp
3314       ctx.typerState.constraint = ctx.typerState.constraint.replace(origin, tp)
3315       tp
3316     }
3317 
3318     /** Instantiate variable from the constraints over its `origin`.
3319      *  If `fromBelow` is true, the variable is instantiated to the lub
3320      *  of its lower bounds in the current constraint; otherwise it is
3321      *  instantiated to the glb of its upper bounds. However, a lower bound
3322      *  instantiation can be a singleton type only if the upper bound
3323      *  is also a singleton type.
3324      */
3325     def instantiate(fromBelow: Boolean)(implicit ctx: Context): Type =
3326       instantiateWith(ctx.typeComparer.instanceType(origin, fromBelow))
3327 
3328     /** For uninstantiated type variables: Is the lower bound different from Nothing? */
3329     def hasLowerBound(implicit ctx: Context) =
3330       !ctx.typerState.constraint.entry(origin).loBound.isBottomType
3331 
3332     /** Unwrap to instance (if instantiated) or origin (if not), until result
3333      *  is no longer a TypeVar
3334      */
3335     override def stripTypeVar(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
3336       val inst = instanceOpt
3337       if (inst.exists) inst.stripTypeVar else origin
3338     }
3339 
3340     /** If the variable is instantiated, its instance, otherwise its origin */
3341     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
3342       val inst = instanceOpt
3343       if (inst.exists) inst
3344       else {
3345         ctx.typerState.ephemeral = true
3346         origin
3347       }
3348     }
3349 
3350     override def computeHash: Int = identityHash
3351     override def equals(that: Any) = this.eq(that.asInstanceOf[AnyRef])
3352 
3353     override def toString = {
3354       def instStr = if (inst.exists) s" -> $inst" else ""
3355       s"TypeVar($origin$instStr)"
3356     }
3357   }
3358 
3359   // ------ ClassInfo, Type Bounds ------------------------------------------------------------
3360 
3361   type TypeOrSymbol = AnyRef /* should be: Type | Symbol */
3362 
3363   /** Roughly: the info of a class during a period.
3364    *  @param prefix       The prefix on which parents, decls, and selfType need to be rebased.
3365    *  @param cls          The class symbol.
3366    *  @param classParents The parent types of this class.
3367    *                      These are all normalized to be TypeRefs by moving any refinements
3368    *                      to be member definitions of the class itself.
3369    *  @param decls        The symbols defined directly in this class.
3370    *  @param selfInfo     The type of `this` in this class, if explicitly given,
3371    *                      NoType otherwise. If class is compiled from source, can also
3372    *                      be a reference to the self symbol containing the type.
3373    */
3374   abstract case class ClassInfo(
3375       prefix: Type,
3376       cls: ClassSymbol,
3377       classParents: List[Type],
3378       decls: Scope,
3379       selfInfo: TypeOrSymbol) extends CachedGroundType with TypeType {
3380 
3381     private[this] var selfTypeCache: Type = null
3382     private[this] var appliedRefCache: Type = null
3383 
3384     /** The self type of a class is the conjunction of
3385      *   - the explicit self type if given (or the info of a given self symbol), and
3386      *   - the fully applied reference to the class itself.
3387      */
3388     def selfType(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
3389       if (selfTypeCache == null)
3390         selfTypeCache = {
3391           val given = cls.givenSelfType
3392           if (!given.exists) appliedRef
3393           else if (cls is Module) given
3394           else if (ctx.erasedTypes) appliedRef
3395           else AndType(given, appliedRef)
3396         }
3397       selfTypeCache
3398     }
3399 
3400     def appliedRef(implicit ctx: Context): Type = {
3401       def clsDenot = if (prefix eq cls.owner.thisType) cls.denot else cls.denot.copySymDenotation(info = this)
3402       if (appliedRefCache == null)
3403         appliedRefCache =
3404           TypeRef(prefix, cls.name, clsDenot).appliedTo(cls.typeParams.map(_.typeRef))
3405       appliedRefCache
3406     }
3407 
3408     // cached because baseType needs parents
3409     private[this] var parentsCache: List[Type] = null
3410 
3411     override def parents(implicit ctx: Context): List[Type] = {
3412       if (parentsCache == null)
3413         parentsCache = classParents.mapConserve(_.asSeenFrom(prefix, cls.owner))
3414       parentsCache
3415     }
3416 
3417     def derivedClassInfo(prefix: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) =
3418       if (prefix eq this.prefix) this
3419       else ClassInfo(prefix, cls, classParents, decls, selfInfo)
3420 
3421     def derivedClassInfo(prefix: Type = this.prefix, classParents: List[Type] = this.classParents, decls: Scope = this.decls, selfInfo: TypeOrSymbol = this.selfInfo)(implicit ctx: Context) =
3422       if ((prefix eq this.prefix) && (classParents eq this.classParents) && (decls eq this.decls) && (selfInfo eq this.selfInfo)) this
3423       else ClassInfo(prefix, cls, classParents, decls, selfInfo)
3424 
3425     override def computeHash = doHash(cls, prefix)
3426 
3427     override def eql(that: Type) = that match {
3428       case that: ClassInfo =>
3429         prefix.eq(that.prefix) &&
3430         cls.eq(that.cls) &&
3431         classParents.eqElements(that.classParents) &&
3432         decls.eq(that.decls) &&
3433         selfInfo.eq(that.selfInfo)
3434       case _ => false
3435     }
3436 
3437     override def toString = s"ClassInfo($prefix, $cls, $classParents)"
3438   }
3439 
3440   class CachedClassInfo(prefix: Type, cls: ClassSymbol, classParents: List[Type], decls: Scope, selfInfo: TypeOrSymbol)
3441     extends ClassInfo(prefix, cls, classParents, decls, selfInfo)
3442 
3443   /** A class for temporary class infos where `parents` are not yet known */
3444   final class TempClassInfo(prefix: Type, cls: ClassSymbol, decls: Scope, selfInfo: TypeOrSymbol)
3445   extends CachedClassInfo(prefix, cls, Nil, decls, selfInfo) {
3446 
3447     /** Install classinfo with known parents in `denot` s */
3448     def finalize(denot: SymDenotation, parents: List[Type])(implicit ctx: Context) =
3449       denot.info = ClassInfo(prefix, cls, parents, decls, selfInfo)
3450 
3451     override def derivedClassInfo(prefix: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) =
3452       if (prefix eq this.prefix) this
3453       else new TempClassInfo(prefix, cls, decls, selfInfo)
3454 
3455     override def toString = s"TempClassInfo($prefix, $cls)"
3456   }
3457 
3458   object ClassInfo {
3459     def apply(prefix: Type, cls: ClassSymbol, classParents: List[Type], decls: Scope, selfInfo: TypeOrSymbol = NoType)(implicit ctx: Context) =
3460       unique(new CachedClassInfo(prefix, cls, classParents, decls, selfInfo))
3461   }
3462 
3463   /** Type bounds >: lo <: hi */
3464   abstract case class TypeBounds(lo: Type, hi: Type) extends CachedProxyType with TypeType {
3465 
3466     assert(lo.isInstanceOf[TermType], lo)
3467     assert(hi.isInstanceOf[TermType], hi)
3468 
3469     override def underlying(implicit ctx: Context): Type = hi
3470 
3471     /** The non-alias type bounds type with given bounds */
3472     def derivedTypeBounds(lo: Type, hi: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) =
3473       if ((lo eq this.lo) && (hi eq this.hi)) this
3474       else TypeBounds(lo, hi)
3475 
3476     def contains(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = tp match {
3477       case tp: TypeBounds => lo <:< tp.lo && tp.hi <:< hi
3478       case tp: ClassInfo =>
3479         val cls = tp.cls
3480         // Note: Taking a normal typeRef does not work here. A normal ref might contain
3481         // also other information about the named type (e.g. bounds).
3482         contains(
3483           TypeRef(tp.prefix, cls).withDenot(new UniqueRefDenotation(cls, tp, cls.validFor)))
3484       case _ =>
3485         lo <:< tp && tp <:< hi
3486     }
3487 
3488     def & (that: TypeBounds)(implicit ctx: Context): TypeBounds =
3489       if ((this.lo frozen_<:< that.lo) && (that.hi frozen_<:< this.hi)) that
3490       else if ((that.lo frozen_<:< this.lo) && (this.hi frozen_<:< that.hi)) this
3491       else TypeBounds(this.lo | that.lo, this.hi & that.hi)
3492 
3493     def | (that: TypeBounds)(implicit ctx: Context): TypeBounds =
3494       if ((this.lo frozen_<:< that.lo) && (that.hi frozen_<:< this.hi)) this
3495       else if ((that.lo frozen_<:< this.lo) && (this.hi frozen_<:< that.hi)) that
3496       else TypeBounds(this.lo & that.lo, this.hi | that.hi)
3497 
3498     override def & (that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = that match {
3499       case that: TypeBounds => this & that
3500       case _ => super.& (that)
3501     }
3502 
3503     override def | (that: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = that match {
3504       case that: TypeBounds => this | that
3505       case _ => super.| (that)
3506     }
3507 
3508     override def computeHash = doHash(lo, hi)
3509 
3510     override def equals(that: Any): Boolean = that match {
3511       case that: TypeAlias => false
3512       case that: TypeBounds => lo == that.lo && hi == that.hi
3513       case _ => false
3514     }
3515 
3516     override def eql(that: Type) = that match {
3517       case that: TypeAlias => false
3518       case that: TypeBounds => lo.eq(that.lo) && hi.eq(that.hi)
3519       case _ => false
3520     }
3521   }
3522 
3523   class RealTypeBounds(lo: Type, hi: Type) extends TypeBounds(lo, hi)
3524 
3525   abstract class TypeAlias(val alias: Type) extends TypeBounds(alias, alias) {
3526 
3527     /** pre: this is a type alias */
3528     def derivedTypeAlias(alias: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) =
3529       if (alias eq this.alias) this else TypeAlias(alias)
3530 
3531     override def computeHash = doHash(alias)
3532 
3533     override def equals(that: Any): Boolean = that match {
3534       case that: TypeAlias => alias == that.alias
3535       case _ => false
3536     }
3537 
3538     override def eql(that: Type): Boolean = that match {
3539       case that: TypeAlias => alias.eq(that.alias)
3540       case _ => false
3541     }
3542   }
3543 
3544   class CachedTypeAlias(alias: Type) extends TypeAlias(alias)
3545 
3546   object TypeBounds {
3547     def apply(lo: Type, hi: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): TypeBounds =
3548       unique(new RealTypeBounds(lo, hi))
3549     def empty(implicit ctx: Context) = apply(defn.NothingType, defn.AnyType)
3550     def upper(hi: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = apply(defn.NothingType, hi)
3551     def lower(lo: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = apply(lo, defn.AnyType)
3552   }
3553 
3554   object TypeAlias {
3555     def apply(alias: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) =
3556       unique(new CachedTypeAlias(alias))
3557     def unapply(tp: TypeAlias): Option[Type] = Some(tp.alias)
3558   }

3616   /** A common superclass of `ErrorType` and `TryDynamicCallSite`. Instances of this

3625   object ErrorType {
3626     def apply(msg: => Message)(implicit ctx: Context): ErrorType = {
3627       val et = new ErrorType {
3628         def msg(implicit ctx: Context): Message =
3629           ctx.errorTypeMsg.get(this) match {
3630             case Some(msgFun) => msgFun()
3631             case None => "error message from previous run no longer available"
3632           }
3633       }
3634       ctx.base.errorTypeMsg(et) = () => msg
3635       et
3636     }
3637   }

3646   /** Wildcard type, possibly with bounds */
3647   abstract case class WildcardType(optBounds: Type) extends CachedGroundType with ValueTypeOrWildcard {
3648     def derivedWildcardType(optBounds: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) =
3649       if (optBounds eq this.optBounds) this
3650       else if (!optBounds.exists) WildcardType
3651       else WildcardType(optBounds.asInstanceOf[TypeBounds])
3652 
3653     override def computeHash = doHash(optBounds)
3654 
3655     override def eql(that: Type) = that match {
3656       case that: WildcardType => optBounds.eq(that.optBounds)
3657       case _ => false
3658     }
3659   }

3667   /** An extractor for single abstract method types.
3668    *  A type is a SAM type if it is a reference to a class or trait, which
3669    *
3670    *   - has a single abstract method with a method type (ExprType
3671    *     and PolyType not allowed!)
3672    *   - can be instantiated without arguments or with just () as argument.
3673    *
3674    *  The pattern `SAMType(denot)` matches a SAM type, where `denot` is the
3675    *  denotation of the single abstract method as a member of the type.
3676    */
3677   object SAMType {
3678     def zeroParamClass(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Type = tp match {
3679       case tp: ClassInfo =>
3680         def zeroParams(tp: Type): Boolean = tp.stripPoly match {
3681           case mt: MethodType => mt.paramInfos.isEmpty && !mt.resultType.isInstanceOf[MethodType]
3682           case et: ExprType => true
3683           case _ => false
3684         }
3685         if ((tp.cls is Trait) || zeroParams(tp.cls.primaryConstructor.info)) tp // !!! needs to be adapted once traits have parameters
3686         else NoType
3687       case tp: AppliedType =>
3688         zeroParamClass(tp.superType)
3689       case tp: TypeRef =>
3690         zeroParamClass(tp.underlying)
3691       case tp: RefinedType =>
3692         zeroParamClass(tp.underlying)
3693       case tp: TypeBounds =>
3694         zeroParamClass(tp.underlying)
3695       case tp: TypeVar =>
3696         zeroParamClass(tp.underlying)
3697       case _ =>
3698         NoType
3699     }
3700     def isInstantiatable(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = zeroParamClass(tp) match {
3701       case cinfo: ClassInfo =>
3702         val tref = tp.narrow
3703         val selfType = cinfo.selfType.asSeenFrom(tref, cinfo.cls)
3704         tref <:< selfType
3705       case _ =>
3706         false
3707     }
3708     def unapply(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): Option[SingleDenotation] =
3709       if (isInstantiatable(tp)) {
3710         val absMems = tp.abstractTermMembers
3711         // println(s"absMems: ${absMems map (_.show) mkString ", "}")
3712         if (absMems.size == 1)
3713           absMems.head.info match {
3714             case mt: MethodType if !mt.isParamDependent => Some(absMems.head)
3715             case _ => None
3716           }
3717         else if (tp isRef defn.PartialFunctionClass)
3718           // To maintain compatibility with 2.x, we treat PartialFunction specially,
3719           // pretending it is a SAM type. In the future it would be better to merge
3720           // Function and PartialFunction, have Function1 contain a isDefinedAt method
3721           //     def isDefinedAt(x: T) = true
3722           // and overwrite that method whenever the function body is a sequence of
3723           // case clauses.
3724           absMems.find(_.symbol.name == nme.apply)
3725         else None
3726       }
3727       else None
3728   }
3729 
3730   // ----- TypeMaps --------------------------------------------------------------------
3731 
3732   /** Common base class of TypeMap and TypeAccumulator */
3733   abstract class VariantTraversal {
3734     protected[core] var variance = 1
3735 
3736     @inline protected def atVariance[T](v: Int)(op: => T): T = {
3737       val saved = variance
3738       variance = v
3739       val res = op
3740       variance = saved
3741       res
3742     }
3743   }
3744 
3745   abstract class TypeMap(implicit protected val ctx: Context)
3746   extends VariantTraversal with (Type => Type) { thisMap =>
3747 
3748     protected def stopAtStatic = true
3749 
3750     def apply(tp: Type): Type
3751 
3752     protected def derivedSelect(tp: NamedType, pre: Type): Type =
3753       tp.derivedSelect(pre)
3754     protected def derivedRefinedType(tp: RefinedType, parent: Type, info: Type): Type =
3755       tp.derivedRefinedType(parent, tp.refinedName, info)
3756     protected def derivedRecType(tp: RecType, parent: Type): Type =
3757       tp.rebind(parent)
3758     protected def derivedTypeAlias(tp: TypeAlias, alias: Type): Type =
3759       tp.derivedTypeAlias(alias)
3760     protected def derivedTypeBounds(tp: TypeBounds, lo: Type, hi: Type): Type =
3761       tp.derivedTypeBounds(lo, hi)
3762     protected def derivedSuperType(tp: SuperType, thistp: Type, supertp: Type): Type =
3763       tp.derivedSuperType(thistp, supertp)
3764     protected def derivedAppliedType(tp: AppliedType, tycon: Type, args: List[Type]): Type =
3765       tp.derivedAppliedType(tycon, args)
3766     protected def derivedAndOrType(tp: AndOrType, tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Type =
3767       tp.derivedAndOrType(tp1, tp2)
3768     protected def derivedAnnotatedType(tp: AnnotatedType, underlying: Type, annot: Annotation): Type =
3769       tp.derivedAnnotatedType(underlying, annot)
3770     protected def derivedWildcardType(tp: WildcardType, bounds: Type): Type =
3771       tp.derivedWildcardType(bounds)
3772     protected def derivedClassInfo(tp: ClassInfo, pre: Type): Type =
3773       tp.derivedClassInfo(pre)
3774     protected def derivedJavaArrayType(tp: JavaArrayType, elemtp: Type): Type =
3775       tp.derivedJavaArrayType(elemtp)
3776     protected def derivedExprType(tp: ExprType, restpe: Type): Type =
3777       tp.derivedExprType(restpe)
3778     // note: currying needed  because Scala2 does not support param-dependencies
3779     protected def derivedLambdaType(tp: LambdaType)(formals: List[tp.PInfo], restpe: Type): Type =
3780       tp.derivedLambdaType(tp.paramNames, formals, restpe)
3781 
3782     /** Map this function over given type */
3783     def mapOver(tp: Type): Type = {
3784       record(s"mapOver ${getClass}")
3785       record("mapOver total")
3786       implicit val ctx = this.ctx
3787       tp match {
3788         case tp: NamedType =>
3789           if (stopAtStatic && tp.symbol.isStatic) tp
3790           else {
3791             val prefix1 = atVariance(variance max 0)(this(tp.prefix))
3792               // A prefix is never contravariant. Even if say `p.A` is used in a contravariant
3793               // context, we cannot assume contravariance for `p` because `p`'s lower
3794               // bound might not have a binding for `A` (e.g. the lower bound could be `Nothing`).
3795               // By contrast, covariance does translate to the prefix, since we have that
3796               // if `p <: q` then `p.A <: q.A`, and well-formedness requires that `A` is a member
3797               // of `p`'s upper bound.
3798             derivedSelect(tp, prefix1)
3799           }
3800         case _: ThisType
3801           | _: BoundType
3802           | NoPrefix => tp
3803 
3804         case tp: AppliedType =>
3805           def mapArgs(args: List[Type], tparams: List[ParamInfo]): List[Type] = args match {
3806             case arg :: otherArgs =>
3807               val arg1 = arg match {
3808                 case arg: TypeBounds => this(arg)
3809                 case arg => atVariance(variance * tparams.head.paramVariance)(this(arg))
3810               }
3811               val otherArgs1 = mapArgs(otherArgs, tparams.tail)
3812               if ((arg1 eq arg) && (otherArgs1 eq otherArgs)) args
3813               else arg1 :: otherArgs1
3814             case nil =>
3815               nil
3816           }
3817           derivedAppliedType(tp, this(tp.tycon), mapArgs(tp.args, tp.typeParams))
3818 
3819         case tp: RefinedType =>
3820           derivedRefinedType(tp, this(tp.parent), this(tp.refinedInfo))
3821 
3822         case tp: TypeAlias =>
3823           derivedTypeAlias(tp, atVariance(0)(this(tp.alias)))
3824 
3825         case tp: TypeBounds =>
3826           variance = -variance
3827           val lo1 = this(tp.lo)
3828           variance = -variance
3829           derivedTypeBounds(tp, lo1, this(tp.hi))
3830 
3831         case tp: RecType =>
3832           derivedRecType(tp, this(tp.parent))
3833 
3834         case tp: TypeVar =>
3835           val inst = tp.instanceOpt
3836           if (inst.exists) apply(inst) else tp
3837 
3838         case tp: ExprType =>
3839           derivedExprType(tp, this(tp.resultType))
3840 
3841         case tp: LambdaType =>
3842           def mapOverLambda = {
3843             variance = -variance
3844             val ptypes1 = tp.paramInfos.mapConserve(this).asInstanceOf[List[tp.PInfo]]
3845             variance = -variance
3846             derivedLambdaType(tp)(ptypes1, this(tp.resultType))
3847           }
3848           mapOverLambda
3849 
3850         case tp @ SuperType(thistp, supertp) =>
3851           derivedSuperType(tp, this(thistp), this(supertp))
3852 
3853         case tp: LazyRef =>
3854           LazyRef(_ => this(tp.ref))
3855 
3856         case tp: ClassInfo =>
3857           mapClassInfo(tp)
3858 
3859          case tp: AndOrType =>
3860           derivedAndOrType(tp, this(tp.tp1), this(tp.tp2))
3861 
3862         case tp: SkolemType =>
3863           tp
3864 
3865         case tp @ AnnotatedType(underlying, annot) =>
3866           val underlying1 = this(underlying)
3867           if (underlying1 eq underlying) tp
3868           else derivedAnnotatedType(tp, underlying1, mapOver(annot))
3869 
3870         case tp: WildcardType =>
3871           derivedWildcardType(tp, mapOver(tp.optBounds))
3872 
3873         case tp: JavaArrayType =>
3874           derivedJavaArrayType(tp, this(tp.elemType))
3875 
3876         case tp: ProtoType =>
3877           tp.map(this)
3878 
3879         case _ =>
3880           tp
3881       }
3882     }
3883 
3884     private def treeTypeMap = new TreeTypeMap(typeMap = this)
3885 
3886     def mapOver(syms: List[Symbol]): List[Symbol] = ctx.mapSymbols(syms, treeTypeMap)
3887 
3888     def mapOver(scope: Scope): Scope = {
3889       val elems = scope.toList
3890       val elems1 = mapOver(elems)
3891       if (elems1 eq elems) scope
3892       else newScopeWith(elems1: _*)
3893     }
3894 
3895     def mapOver(annot: Annotation): Annotation =
3896       annot.derivedAnnotation(mapOver(annot.tree))
3897 
3898     def mapOver(tree: Tree): Tree = treeTypeMap(tree)
3899 
3900     /** Can be overridden. By default, only the prefix is mapped. */
3901     protected def mapClassInfo(tp: ClassInfo): Type =
3902       derivedClassInfo(tp, this(tp.prefix))
3903 
3904     /** A version of mapClassInfo which also maps parents and self type */
3905     protected def mapFullClassInfo(tp: ClassInfo) =
3906       tp.derivedClassInfo(
3907         prefix = this(tp.prefix),
3908         classParents = tp.classParents.mapConserve(this),
3909         selfInfo = tp.selfInfo match {
3910           case tp: Type => this(tp)
3911           case sym => sym
3912         }
3913       )
3914 
3915     def andThen(f: Type => Type): TypeMap = new TypeMap {
3916       override def stopAtStatic = thisMap.stopAtStatic
3917       def apply(tp: Type) = f(thisMap(tp))
3918     }
3919   }
3920 
3921   /** A type map that maps also parents and self type of a ClassInfo */
3922   abstract class DeepTypeMap(implicit ctx: Context) extends TypeMap {
3923     override def mapClassInfo(tp: ClassInfo) = {
3924       val prefix1 = this(tp.prefix)
3925       val parents1 = tp.parents mapConserve this
3926       val selfInfo1 = tp.selfInfo match {
3927         case selfInfo: Type => this(selfInfo)
3928         case selfInfo => selfInfo
3929       }
3930       tp.derivedClassInfo(prefix1, parents1, tp.decls, selfInfo1)
3931     }
3932   }

3934   @sharable object IdentityTypeMap extends TypeMap()(NoContext) {
3935     override def stopAtStatic = true
3936     def apply(tp: Type) = tp
3937   }
3938 
3939   /** A type map that approximates TypeBounds types depending on
3940    *  variance.
3941    *
3942    *  if variance > 0 : approximate by upper bound
3943    *     variance < 0 : approximate by lower bound
3944    *     variance = 0 : propagate bounds to next outer level
3945    */
3946   abstract class ApproximatingTypeMap(implicit ctx: Context) extends TypeMap { thisMap =>
3947 
3948     protected def range(lo: Type, hi: Type) =
3949       if (variance > 0) hi
3950       else if (variance < 0) lo
3951       else Range(lower(lo), upper(hi))
3952 
3953     protected def isRange(tp: Type) = tp.isInstanceOf[Range]
3954 
3955     protected def lower(tp: Type) = tp match {
3956       case tp: Range => tp.lo
3957       case _ => tp
3958     }
3959 
3960     protected def upper(tp: Type) = tp match {
3961       case tp: Range => tp.hi
3962       case _ => tp
3963     }
3964 
3965     protected def rangeToBounds(tp: Type) = tp match {
3966       case Range(lo, hi) => TypeBounds(lo, hi)
3967       case _ => tp
3968     }
3969 
3970     /** Try to widen a named type to its info relative to given prefix `pre`, where possible.
3971      *  The possible cases are listed inline in the code.
3972      */
3973     def tryWiden(tp: NamedType, pre: Type): Type = pre.member(tp.name) match {
3974       case d: SingleDenotation =>
3975         d.info.dealias match {
3976           case TypeAlias(alias) =>
3977             // if H#T = U, then for any x in L..H, x.T =:= U,
3978             // hence we can replace with U under all variances
3979             reapply(alias)
3980           case TypeBounds(lo, hi) =>
3981             // If H#T = _ >: S <: U, then for any x in L..H, S <: x.T <: U,
3982             // hence we can replace with S..U under all variances
3983             range(atVariance(-variance)(reapply(lo)), reapply(hi))
3984           case info: SingletonType =>
3985             // if H#x: y.type, then for any x in L..H, x.type =:= y.type,
3986             // hence we can replace with y.type under all variances
3987             reapply(info)
3988           case _ =>
3989             NoType
3990         }
3991       case _ => NoType
3992     }
3993 
3994     /** Expand parameter reference corresponding to prefix `pre`;
3995      *  If the expansion is a wildcard parameter reference, convert its
3996      *  underlying bounds to a range, otherwise return the expansion.
3997      */
3998     def expandParam(tp: NamedType, pre: Type) = tp.argForParam(pre) match {
3999       case arg @ TypeRef(pre, _) if pre.isArgPrefixOf(arg.symbol) =>
4000         arg.info match {
4001           case TypeBounds(lo, hi) => range(atVariance(-variance)(reapply(lo)), reapply(hi))
4002           case arg => reapply(arg)
4003         }
4004       case arg => reapply(arg)
4005     }
4006 
4007     /** Derived selection.
4008      *  @pre   the (upper bound of) prefix `pre` has a member named `tp.name`.
4009      */
4010     override protected def derivedSelect(tp: NamedType, pre: Type) =
4011       if (pre eq tp.prefix) tp
4012       else pre match {
4013         case Range(preLo, preHi) =>
4014           val forwarded =
4015             if (tp.symbol.is(ClassTypeParam)) expandParam(tp, preHi)
4016             else tryWiden(tp, preHi)
4017           forwarded.orElse(
4018             range(super.derivedSelect(tp, preLo), super.derivedSelect(tp, preHi)))
4019         case _ =>
4020           super.derivedSelect(tp, pre)
4021       }
4022 
4023     override protected def derivedRefinedType(tp: RefinedType, parent: Type, info: Type) =
4024       if ((parent eq tp.parent) && (info eq tp.refinedInfo)) tp
4025       else parent match {
4026         case Range(parentLo, parentHi) =>
4027           range(derivedRefinedType(tp, parentLo, info), derivedRefinedType(tp, parentHi, info))
4028         case _ =>
4029           def propagate(lo: Type, hi: Type) =
4030             range(derivedRefinedType(tp, parent, lo), derivedRefinedType(tp, parent, hi))
4031           if (parent.isBottomType) parent
4032           else info match {
4033             case Range(infoLo: TypeBounds, infoHi: TypeBounds) =>
4034               assert(variance == 0)
4035               if (!infoLo.isAlias && !infoHi.isAlias) propagate(infoLo, infoHi)
4036               else range(tp.bottomType, tp.parent)
4037             case Range(infoLo, infoHi) =>
4038               propagate(infoLo, infoHi)
4039             case _ =>
4040               tp.derivedRefinedType(parent, tp.refinedName, info)
4041           }
4042         }
4043 
4044     override protected def derivedRecType(tp: RecType, parent: Type) =
4045       if (parent eq tp.parent) tp
4046       else parent match {
4047         case Range(lo, hi) => range(tp.rebind(lo), tp.rebind(hi))
4048         case _ => tp.rebind(parent)
4049       }
4050 
4051     override protected def derivedTypeAlias(tp: TypeAlias, alias: Type) =
4052       if (alias eq tp.alias) tp
4053       else alias match {
4054         case Range(lo, hi) =>
4055           if (variance > 0) TypeBounds(lo, hi)
4056           else range(TypeAlias(lo), TypeAlias(hi))
4057         case _ => tp.derivedTypeAlias(alias)
4058       }
4059 
4060     override protected def derivedTypeBounds(tp: TypeBounds, lo: Type, hi: Type) =
4061       if ((lo eq tp.lo) && (hi eq tp.hi)) tp
4062       else if (isRange(lo) || isRange(hi))
4063         if (variance > 0) TypeBounds(lower(lo), upper(hi))
4064         else range(TypeBounds(upper(lo), lower(hi)), TypeBounds(lower(lo), upper(hi)))
4065       else tp.derivedTypeBounds(lo, hi)
4066 
4067     override protected def derivedSuperType(tp: SuperType, thistp: Type, supertp: Type) =
4068       if (isRange(thistp) || isRange(supertp)) range(thistp.bottomType, thistp.topType)
4069       else tp.derivedSuperType(thistp, supertp)
4070 
4071     override protected def derivedAppliedType(tp: AppliedType, tycon: Type, args: List[Type]): Type =
4072       tycon match {
4073         case Range(tyconLo, tyconHi) =>
4074           range(derivedAppliedType(tp, tyconLo, args), derivedAppliedType(tp, tyconHi, args))
4075         case _ =>
4076           if (args.exists(isRange)) {
4077             if (variance > 0) tp.derivedAppliedType(tycon, args.map(rangeToBounds))
4078             else {
4079               val loBuf, hiBuf = new mutable.ListBuffer[Type]
4080               // Given `C[A1, ..., An]` where sone A's are ranges, try to find
4081               // non-range arguments L1, ..., Ln and H1, ..., Hn such that
4082               // C[L1, ..., Ln] <: C[H1, ..., Hn] by taking the right limits of
4083               // ranges that appear in as co- or contravariant arguments.
4084               // Fail for non-variant argument ranges.
4085               // If successful, the L-arguments are in loBut, the H-arguments in hiBuf.
4086               // @return  operation succeeded for all arguments.
4087               def distributeArgs(args: List[Type], tparams: List[ParamInfo]): Boolean = args match {
4088                 case Range(lo, hi) :: args1 =>
4089                   val v = tparams.head.paramVariance
4090                   if (v == 0) false
4091                   else {
4092                     if (v > 0) { loBuf += lo; hiBuf += hi }
4093                     else { loBuf += hi; hiBuf += lo }
4094                     distributeArgs(args1, tparams.tail)
4095                   }
4096                 case arg :: args1 =>
4097                   loBuf += arg; hiBuf += arg
4098                   distributeArgs(args1, tparams.tail)
4099                 case nil =>
4100                   true
4101               }
4102               if (distributeArgs(args, tp.typeParams))
4103                 range(tp.derivedAppliedType(tycon, loBuf.toList),
4104                       tp.derivedAppliedType(tycon, hiBuf.toList))
4105               else range(tp.bottomType, tp.topType)
4106                 // TODO: can we give a better bound than `topType`?
4107             }
4108           }
4109           else tp.derivedAppliedType(tycon, args)
4110       }
4111 
4112     override protected def derivedAndOrType(tp: AndOrType, tp1: Type, tp2: Type) =
4113       if (isRange(tp1) || isRange(tp2))
4114         if (tp.isAnd) range(lower(tp1) & lower(tp2), upper(tp1) & upper(tp2))
4115         else range(lower(tp1) | lower(tp2), upper(tp1) | upper(tp2))
4116       else tp.derivedAndOrType(tp1, tp2)
4117 
4118     override protected def derivedAnnotatedType(tp: AnnotatedType, underlying: Type, annot: Annotation) =
4119       underlying match {
4120         case Range(lo, hi) =>
4121           range(tp.derivedAnnotatedType(lo, annot), tp.derivedAnnotatedType(hi, annot))
4122         case _ =>
4123           if (underlying.isBottomType) underlying
4124           else tp.derivedAnnotatedType(underlying, annot)
4125       }
4126     override protected def derivedWildcardType(tp: WildcardType, bounds: Type) = {
4127       tp.derivedWildcardType(rangeToBounds(bounds))
4128     }
4129 
4130     override protected def derivedClassInfo(tp: ClassInfo, pre: Type): Type = {
4131       assert(!isRange(pre))
4132         // we don't know what to do here; this case has to be handled in subclasses
4133         // (typically by handling ClassInfo's specially, in case they can be encountered).
4134       tp.derivedClassInfo(pre)
4135     }
4136 
4137     override protected def derivedLambdaType(tp: LambdaType)(formals: List[tp.PInfo], restpe: Type): Type =
4138       restpe match {
4139         case Range(lo, hi) =>
4140           range(derivedLambdaType(tp)(formals, lo), derivedLambdaType(tp)(formals, hi))
4141         case _ =>
4142           tp.derivedLambdaType(tp.paramNames, formals, restpe)
4143       }
4144 
4145     protected def reapply(tp: Type): Type = apply(tp)
4146   }
4147 
4148   /** A range of possible types between lower bound `lo` and upper bound `hi`.
4149    *  Only used internally in `ApproximatingTypeMap`.
4150    */
4151   private case class Range(lo: Type, hi: Type) extends UncachedGroundType {
4152     assert(!lo.isInstanceOf[Range])
4153     assert(!hi.isInstanceOf[Range])
4154 
4155     override def toText(printer: Printer): Text =
4156       lo.toText(printer) ~ ".." ~ hi.toText(printer)
4157   }

4159   // ----- TypeAccumulators ----------------------------------------------------
4160 
4161   abstract class TypeAccumulator[T](implicit protected val ctx: Context)
4162   extends VariantTraversal with ((T, Type) => T) {
4163 
4164     protected def stopAtStatic = true
4165 
4166     def apply(x: T, tp: Type): T
4167 
4168     protected def applyToAnnot(x: T, annot: Annotation): T = x // don't go into annotations
4169 
4170     protected final def applyToPrefix(x: T, tp: NamedType) =
4171       atVariance(variance max 0)(this(x, tp.prefix)) // see remark on NamedType case in TypeMap
4172 
4173     def foldOver(x: T, tp: Type): T = {
4174       record(s"foldOver $getClass")
4175       record(s"foldOver total")
4176       tp match {
4177       case tp: TypeRef =>
4178         if (stopAtStatic && tp.symbol.isStatic) x
4179         else {
4180           val tp1 = tp.prefix.lookupRefined(tp.name)
4181           if (tp1.exists) this(x, tp1) else applyToPrefix(x, tp)
4182         }
4183 
4184       case tp @ AppliedType(tycon, args) =>
4185         @tailrec def foldArgs(x: T, tparams: List[ParamInfo], args: List[Type]): T =
4186           if (args.isEmpty) {
4187             assert(tparams.isEmpty)
4188             x
4189           }
4190           else {
4191             val tparam = tparams.head
4192             val acc = args.head match {
4193               case arg: TypeBounds => this(x, arg)
4194               case arg => atVariance(variance * tparam.paramVariance)(this(x, arg))
4195             }
4196             foldArgs(acc, tparams.tail, args.tail)
4197           }
4198         foldArgs(this(x, tycon), tp.typeParams, args)
4199 
4200       case _: BoundType | _: ThisType => x
4201 
4202       case tp: LambdaType =>
4203         variance = -variance
4204         val y = foldOver(x, tp.paramInfos)
4205         variance = -variance
4206         this(y, tp.resultType)
4207 
4208       case NoPrefix => x
4209 
4210       case tp: TermRef =>
4211         if (stopAtStatic && tp.currentSymbol.isStatic) x
4212         else applyToPrefix(x, tp)
4213 
4214       case tp: TypeVar =>
4215         this(x, tp.underlying)
4216 
4217       case ExprType(restpe) =>
4218         this(x, restpe)
4219 
4220       case bounds @ TypeBounds(lo, hi) =>
4221         if (lo eq hi) atVariance(0)(this(x, lo))
4222         else {
4223           variance = -variance
4224           val y = this(x, lo)
4225           variance = -variance
4226           this(y, hi)
4227         }
4228 
4229       case tp: AndOrType =>
4230         this(this(x, tp.tp1), tp.tp2)
4231 
4232       case AnnotatedType(underlying, annot) =>
4233         this(applyToAnnot(x, annot), underlying)
4234 
4235       case tp: ProtoType =>
4236         tp.fold(x, this)
4237 
4238       case tp: RefinedType =>
4239         this(this(x, tp.parent), tp.refinedInfo)
4240 
4241       case tp: WildcardType =>
4242         this(x, tp.optBounds)
4243 
4244       case tp @ ClassInfo(prefix, _, _, _, _) =>
4245         this(x, prefix)
4246 
4247       case tp: JavaArrayType =>
4248         this(x, tp.elemType)
4249 
4250       case tp: SkolemType =>
4251         this(x, tp.info)
4252 
4253       case SuperType(thistp, supertp) =>
4254         this(this(x, thistp), supertp)
4255 
4256       case tp: LazyRef =>
4257         this(x, tp.ref)
4258 
4259       case tp: RecType =>
4260         this(x, tp.parent)
4261 
4262       case _ => x
4263     }}
4264 
4265     @tailrec final def foldOver(x: T, ts: List[Type]): T = ts match {
4266       case t :: ts1 => foldOver(apply(x, t), ts1)
4267       case nil => x
4268     }
4269   }
4270 
4271   abstract class TypeTraverser(implicit ctx: Context) extends TypeAccumulator[Unit] {
4272     def traverse(tp: Type): Unit
4273     def apply(x: Unit, tp: Type): Unit = traverse(tp)
4274     protected def traverseChildren(tp: Type) = foldOver((), tp)
4275   }
4276 
4277   class ExistsAccumulator(p: Type => Boolean, forceLazy: Boolean = true)(implicit ctx: Context) extends TypeAccumulator[Boolean] {
4278     override def stopAtStatic = false
4279     def apply(x: Boolean, tp: Type) =
4280       x || p(tp) || (forceLazy || !tp.isInstanceOf[LazyRef]) && foldOver(x, tp)
4281   }
4282 
4283   class ForeachAccumulator(p: Type => Unit, override val stopAtStatic: Boolean)(implicit ctx: Context) extends TypeAccumulator[Unit] {
4284     def apply(x: Unit, tp: Type): Unit = foldOver(p(tp), tp)
4285   }
4286 
4287   class NamedPartsAccumulator(p: NamedType => Boolean, excludeLowerBounds: Boolean = false)
4288     (implicit ctx: Context) extends TypeAccumulator[mutable.Set[NamedType]] {
4289     override def stopAtStatic = false
4290     def maybeAdd(x: mutable.Set[NamedType], tp: NamedType) = if (p(tp)) x += tp else x
4291     val seen: mutable.Set[Type] = mutable.Set()
4292     def apply(x: mutable.Set[NamedType], tp: Type): mutable.Set[NamedType] =
4293       if (seen contains tp) x
4294       else {
4295         seen += tp
4296         tp match {
4297           case tp: TypeRef =>
4298             foldOver(maybeAdd(x, tp), tp)
4299           case tp: ThisType =>
4300             apply(x, tp.tref)
4301           case NoPrefix =>
4302             foldOver(x, tp)
4303           case tp: TermRef =>
4304             apply(foldOver(maybeAdd(x, tp), tp), tp.underlying)
4305           case tp: AppliedType =>
4306             foldOver(x, tp)
4307           case TypeBounds(lo, hi) =>
4308             if (!excludeLowerBounds) apply(x, lo)
4309             apply(x, hi)
4310           case tp: ParamRef =>
4311             apply(x, tp.underlying)
4312           case tp: ConstantType =>
4313             apply(x, tp.underlying)
4314           case _ =>
4315             foldOver(x, tp)
4316         }
4317       }
4318   }

4320   //   ----- Name Filters --------------------------------------------------
4321 
4322   /** A name filter selects or discards a member name of a type `pre`.
4323    *  To enable efficient caching, name filters have to satisfy the
4324    *  following invariant: If `keep` is a name filter, and `pre` has
4325    *  class `C` as a base class, then
4326    *
4327    *    keep(pre, name)  implies  keep(C.this, name)
4328    */
4329   abstract class NameFilter {
4330     def apply(pre: Type, name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean
4331   }
4332 
4333   /** A filter for names of abstract types of a given type */
4334   object abstractTypeNameFilter extends NameFilter {
4335     def apply(pre: Type, name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
4336       name.isTypeName && {
4337         val mbr = pre.nonPrivateMember(name)
4338         (mbr.symbol is Deferred) && mbr.info.isInstanceOf[RealTypeBounds]
4339       }
4340   }
4341 
4342   /** A filter for names of abstract types of a given type */
4343   object nonClassTypeNameFilter extends NameFilter {
4344     def apply(pre: Type, name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
4345       name.isTypeName && {
4346         val mbr = pre.member(name)
4347         mbr.symbol.isType && !mbr.symbol.isClass
4348       }
4349   }
4350 
4351   /** A filter for names of deferred term definitions of a given type */
4352   object abstractTermNameFilter extends NameFilter {
4353     def apply(pre: Type, name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
4354       name.isTermName && pre.nonPrivateMember(name).hasAltWith(_.symbol is Deferred)
4355   }
4356 
4357   /** A filter for names of type aliases of a given type */
4358   object typeAliasNameFilter extends NameFilter {
4359     def apply(pre: Type, name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
4360       name.isTypeName && {
4361         val mbr = pre.nonPrivateMember(name)
4362         mbr.symbol.isAliasType
4363       }
4364   }
4365 
4366   object typeNameFilter extends NameFilter {
4367     def apply(pre: Type, name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = name.isTypeName
4368   }
4369 
4370   object fieldFilter extends NameFilter {
4371     def apply(pre: Type, name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean =
4372       name.isTermName && (pre member name).hasAltWith(!_.symbol.is(Method))
4373   }
4374 
4375   object takeAllFilter extends NameFilter {
4376     def apply(pre: Type, name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = true
4377   }
4378 
4379   object implicitFilter extends NameFilter {
4380     /** A dummy filter method.
4381      *  Implicit filtering is handled specially in computeMemberNames, so
4382      *  no post-filtering is needed.
4383      */
4384     def apply(pre: Type, name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context): Boolean = true
4385   }

4395   class MissingType(pre: Type, name: Name)(implicit ctx: Context) extends TypeError(
4396     i"""cannot resolve reference to type $pre.$name
4397        |the classfile defining the type might be missing from the classpath${otherReason(pre)}""") {

4399   }

4401   private def otherReason(pre: Type)(implicit ctx: Context): String = pre match {
4402     case pre: ThisType if pre.cls.givenSelfType.exists =>
4403       i"\nor the self type of $pre might not contain all transitive dependencies"
4404     case _ => ""

4407   class CyclicReference private (val denot: SymDenotation)
4408     extends TypeError(s"cyclic reference involving $denot") {
4409     def toMessage(implicit ctx: Context) = CyclicReferenceInvolving(denot)
4410   }

4412   object CyclicReference {
4413     def apply(denot: SymDenotation)(implicit ctx: Context): CyclicReference = {
4414       val ex = new CyclicReference(denot)
4415       if (!(ctx.mode is Mode.CheckCyclic)) {
4416         cyclicErrors.println(ex.getMessage)
4417         for (elem <- ex.getStackTrace take 200)
4418           cyclicErrors.println(elem.toString)
4419       }
4420       ex
4421     }
4422   }
